i think our company has experienced every setback imaginable. 
a limited startup budget.💰
2 computer crashes 💻. current data unable to recover. 
my cellphone was stolen on vacation 📲

not one ☝️ subscription purchased in november or december. •
•

your testimony, business, ministry, story is for others to hear and learn from. to experience and be transformed. •
•

so, our message for you today is just keep going! follow your heart 💕straight towards your purpose! •

text_retweet:
repost from @saraalay using @repostregramapp - we teach our children all sorts of ways to keep themselves safe.
but do we teach them about #bodysafety?
we tempt to think our children are safe or too young to face such matters or to learn about it and because it is culturally not acceptable to talk about this issue in our society it is not being taught in our children’s schools.
.
13 years ago when i was a teacher i was aware of some disturbing behaviors in my class but i lacked the knowledge to address  this matter and would be hesitant as i hated to be wrong or jump to any conclusions.
.
we have educators who are wonderful and amazing with our children but fear this issue or don’t know how to deal with it because they are not trained to do so.
.
we need to educate our young ones how to protect themselves and how to say no.
body safety education should be added to our curriculums, parents should discuss body safety with their children the web is full of materials and videos that help parents to do so and these 👆🏽👆🏽👆🏽 are helpful books available at amazon.com
.
@shadesofinjera has started a #metooethiopia movement ,read the disturbing stories victims of sexual assault shared in their ig and please sign the petition to ask @pmabiyahmed to address this issue.
.

text:
this week has been a difficult one for us discipline wise, and it all started because i felt too lazy to go grocery shopping last saturday. now i don’t really like grocery shopping but it is so important. when i neglect this it makes it really hard for us to not spend money eating out. we went over budget $40 which we will deduct from this week’s envelopes, but it impacts so much more than money. we feel bad (physically and emotionally) when we don’t have healthy good food and we are always eating out. we feel bad when we don’t have food for lunches and either go without or buy something. and it starts to impact other areas as well. we have not been on a good sleep pattern this week. going to bed too late and rushing out the door. not taking time to make the right things our priority. but the good thing about friday is it means the end of one week of bad habits and the chance to change this for next week. i find it is in taking responsibility and doing the things we don’t want that we find real freedom and peace of mind. can anyone else relate to this? happy friday all, here’s to a fresh new week.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
hoy estoy de cumpleaños 🎂❤️ ! lo que más deseo es que mi país llamado venezuela este en libertad 💛💙❤️🇻🇪
.
.
.
gracias a dios por permitirme otro año más de vida, por ponerme retos en este año por la cual debo luchar y seguir adelante, por conocer personas nuevas y maravillosas llenas de buena vibra y bendiciones en multitud. una nueva familia, unos compañeros de trabajo excelentes, y sobretodo una persona que jamás olvidare por nada en el mundo por la cual debo luchar y seguir adelante para dar la cara delante ella. esa persona es mi madre por darme este crecimiento y mi educación que hasta ahora he aprendido y he crecido más. .
.
.
.
allí es cuando agradeces y dices: 
el tiempo de dios es perfecto! .
.
.
.
.
hoy en día agradezco tanto tu compañía tu guía y tus regaños, y sobre todo tus abrazos que dejan que mi corazón se me pare por un momento para que el vuelva a retomar su camino! gracias osjogaya

text:
pour un projet littéraire je suis à la recherche de témoignages de victimes de violences sexuelles.

chaque témoignage sera scindé en différentes parties :

1- comment avez-vous réagit au moment du viol ou de l’agression sexuelle (figement, fuite, combat, etc…) 2- comment avez-vous été reçu(e)s au commissariat ou à la gendarmerie lors de votre plainte ?

3- si vous n’avez pas porté plainte, pouvez-vous en donner la raison ?

4- en avez-vous parlé à votre entourage? si oui, comment ont-ils réagit? vous soutiennent-ils encore à l’heure actuelle?

5- votre plainte a-t-elle fait l’objet d’un classement sans suite, d’un non-lieu, d’une relaxe ou d’un acquittement? ou à l’inverse l’agresseur a-t-il été condamné? comment avez-vous vécu cela?

6- quelles investigations ont été menées durant l’enquête ? (expertises, témoignages, analyses adn, etc…) 7- quel a été votre parcours psychologique après l’agression?

8 – quelles ont été les conséquences sur votre vie familiale?

9- quelles ont été les conséquences sur votre vie scolaire, professionnelle?

10- quelles ont été les conséquences sur votre vie amoureuse? sur votre sexualité?

11- plus largement quels sont les changements que vous percevez depuis l’agression?

12- comment voyez-vous votre corps? avez-vous constaté des changements physiques depuis les faits? avez-vous des troubles alimentaires?

13- avez-vous souffert d’amnésie traumatique?

14- qu’avez-vous entrepris pour vous sentir mieux? (sport, yoga, théâtre, relaxation, etc…) 15- quelles sont les thérapies qui fonctionnent selon votre expériences? (emdr, tcc, hypnose, etc…) 16- si vous pouviez donner des conseils à des victimes que diriez-vous?

text:
we need to as a society begin to teach younger men and men in general to know how to control themselves. 
i'm tired of hearing "men think with their penises" as an excuse for rapey behaviour. 
men don't think with their penises, they think with their heads and their heads tell them that if they can't control themselves, society would not hold them accountable
.
we need to create a better society for the next generation of nigerian women and girls where we can move at night without the fear of rape. 
where we are not at war with our bodies. 
where we don't hate our bodies because they bring unwanted touch from slimy men
.
let's do better and teach men that no woman's body is their exclusive property. 
let's hold men accountable because in my almost twenty years, i've never heard anyone say "she thinks with her vagina" as an excuse for rape. 
enough said
.
.
.

text:
we teach our children all sorts of ways to keep themselves safe.
but do we teach them about #bodysafety?
we tempt to think our children are safe or too young to face such matters or to learn about it and because it is culturally not acceptable to talk about this issue in our society it is not being taught in our children’s schools.
.
13 years ago when i was a teacher i was aware of some disturbing behaviors in my class but i lacked the knowledge to address  this matter and would be hesitant as i hated to be wrong or jump to any conclusions.
.
we have educators who are wonderful and amazing with our children but fear this issue or don’t know how to deal with it because they are not trained to do so.
.
we need to educate our young ones how to protect themselves and how to say no.
body safety education should be added to our curriculums, parents should discuss body safety with their children the web is full of materials and videos that help parents to do so and these 👆🏽👆🏽👆🏽 are helpful books available at amazon.com
.
@shadesofinjera has started a #metooethiopia movement ,read the disturbing stories victims of sexual assault shared in their ig and please sign the petition to ask @pmabiyahmed to address this issue.
.
#sexualassault #sexualeducation #ethiopia #addisababa #rapeculture #rapevictims #rapevictimsupport #bodysafetyeducation #shadesofinjera #eritrea #metooeritrea #metoo #metoomovement

"איזו רזה היא, היא חייבת לעשות חזה" "כן" "תקשיבי רגע נטלי, יש לך גוף, גוף פצצה. ואת חייבת.. אבל תהיי ראש פתוח. את צריכה טיפה לעשות חזה ואת תהיי מושלמת." רגע, זה לא נגמר, "למה את לא יכולה?.. את מושלמת, יש לך גוף נדיר. אין לי מילים. אני מסתכל על החיצוניות, טיפה, אם היה לך עוד טיפה." ועוד משפט אחד: "כאילו אני לא יכול לשאול את זה?"
אז ככה, אני נערה. עדיין לא אישה וכבר לא ילדה, ממש בגבול שבין השניים. לצערי, במעט השנים שאני חיה חוויתי לא מעט הטרדות מיניות. נכון, זה נגיעות בישבן במסיבות, כי כנראה המכנס הקצר שאני כל כך אוהבת ולא כל כך קצר, נותן אישור לילדים, גברים ונערים לגעת בו ולבדוק עד כמה בדיוק הוא ארוך או קצר. וכן, זה המבטים האלה שגברים בני 40, 50 ואפילו 60 נותנים לך כמו כלב מיוחם על הכלבה בדשא. וכן כן, לא טעיתם, זה המילים: "איזו כוסית" "וואלה אם היית קצת יותר גדולה, מה הייתי עושה לך" "וואי וואי זה אמיתי" ועוד אלף דוגמאות שכל אחת יכולה להשלים כבר לבד. גברים, אני רוצה להפתיע אתכם, כל הנגיעות, המבטים או המילים, זו לא מחמאה. או משהו שקרוב. עוברת לי חלחלה בכל הגוף כשגברים מסתכלים עליי לכל איזור, חשוף או מוסתר וכל מילה שלא עוברת את המסנן פה שלכם מעוררת בי בחילה. והבורות, והבורות. החוסר מודעות הזה כבר חונק אותי.
אוי, והדימוי גוף. כשהייתי מדריכה בצופים החלטתי שאני מקדישה לזה את רוב תשומת הלב ועד כמה שאני יכולה להדגיש ולהעביר את המסר הכל כך עוצמתי שמסתתר מאחורי צמד המילים האלו. כל אישה, אני מדגישה, כ ל  א י ש ה לא שלמה עם הגוף שלה. באיזשהו גיל, שעוד רחוק ממני, את מבינה שזה מה שיש או שאת עובדת וקורעת את עצמך כדי להגיע לדבר הכי קרוב שסימנת לעצמך, אבל את עדיין לא שלמה עם עצמך, אז את פשוט אוהבת את עצמך, מתחילה לאהוב את הקילו הזה שהצטרף ליד או את הקמט הקטן הזה במצח, ואפילו את החזה שלך, למרות שכל כך רצית וניסית שהוא יהיה כמו בחלום.
ואז מגיע אדם, שבשניה אחת שובר את כל התהליך שעשית, שבנית, שחווית. וכמה אפשר לגלות על אדם במשפט אחד.
עדי לאון, גבר כבן 40, נשוי ואב לשלושה ילדים, הוא האדם ששבר את הכללים ואת כל הקודים שניסינו לבנות כחברה בשנים האחרונות ובפרט 2018. מבהירה שלא הכרתי את האדם ואת הדמות לעולם ואין לי שום דבר נגדו. עד עכשיו. מה שעדי עשה זה לא הערה חברותית וגם לא הערה בונה, זו הטרדה מינית לכל דבר. אני לא יכולה לתאר את ההתכווצות שיש לי בלב בכל פעם שאני רואה את הסרטון הזה.

'' אז ככה , אני נערה . עדיין לא אישה וכבר לא ילדה , ממש בגבול שבין השניים . לצערי , במעט השנים שאני חיה חוויתי לא מעט הטרדות מיניות . נכון , זה נגיעות בישבן במסיבות , כי כנראה המכנס הקצר שאני כל כך אוהבת ולא כל כך קצר , נותן אישור לילדים , גברים ונערים לגעת בו ולבדוק עד כמה בדיוק הוא ארוך או קצר . וכן , זה המבטים האלה שגברים בני 40 , 50 ואפילו 60 נותנים לך כמו כלב מיוחם על הכלבה בדשא . וכן כן , לא טעיתם , זה המילים : `` איזו כוסית '' `` וואלה אם היית קצת יותר גדולה , מה הייתי עושה לך '' `` וואי וואי זה אמיתי '' ועוד אלף דוגמאות שכל אחת יכולה להשלים כבר לבד . גברים , אני רוצה להפתיע אתכם , כל הנגיעות , המבטים או המילים , זו לא מחמאה . או משהו שקרוב . עוברת לי חלחלה בכל הגוף כשגברים מסתכלים עליי לכל איזור , חשוף או מוסתר וכל מילה שלא עוברת את המסנן פה שלכם מעוררת בי בחילה . והבורות , והבורות . החוסר מודעות הזה כבר חונק אותי . אוי , והדימוי גוף . כשהייתי מדריכה בצופים החלטתי שאני מקדישה לזה את רוב תשומת הלב ועד כמה שאני יכולה להדגיש ולהעביר את המסר הכל כך עוצמתי שמסתתר מאחורי צמד המילים האלו . כל אישה , אני מדגישה , כ ל א י ש ה לא שלמה עם הגוף שלה . באיזשהו גיל , שעוד רחוק ממני , את מבינה שזה מה שיש או שאת עובדת וקורעת את עצמך כדי להגיע לדבר הכי קרוב שסימנת לעצמך , אבל את עדיין לא שלמה עם עצמך , אז את פשוט אוהבת את עצמך , מתחילה לאהוב את הקילו הזה שהצטרף ליד או את הקמט הקטן הזה במצח , ואפילו את החזה שלך , למרות שכל כך רצית וניסית שהוא יהיה כמו בחלום . ואז מגיע אדם , שבשניה אחת שובר את כל התהליך שעשית , שבנית , שחווית . וכמה אפשר לגלות על אדם במשפט אחד . עדי לאון , גבר כבן 40 , נשוי ואב לשלושה ילדים , הוא האדם ששבר את הכללים ואת כל הקודים שניסינו לבנות כחברה בשנים האחרונות ובפרט 2018 . מבהירה שלא הכרתי את האדם ואת הדמות לעולם ואין לי שום דבר נגדו . עד עכשיו . מה שעדי עשה זה לא הערה חברותית וגם לא הערה בונה , זו הטרדה מינית לכל דבר . אני לא יכולה לתאר את ההתכווצות שיש לי בלב בכל פעם שאני רואה את הסרטון הזה .

we might not often think about how important and necessary shelters are for people escaping domestic and sexual violence. this is a beautiful and inspiring reminder to us all! thank you so much, anamaria!

text:
‪one of the greatest current issues is lack of value for life. it’s not just children. it rears it’s head in human trafficking, racism, mass shootings, abuse, and so much more. worldwide there is a lack of value for human life. people become items/objects to be used or disposed of, instead human beings created to be loved. ‬

we are not apes, wild animals, nor objects. we are made in the image of god and each person of significant worth. when we know how much god values us, all human life-it changes the way we treat others. 
people are not objects to be used. 
people are not commodities to be sold. 
people are not pleasure centers to be exploited. 
people are not punching bags to be abused. 
people are not images to be lusted over. 
people are not slaves to do our bidding. 
people are not mindless drones to be dominated or controlled. 
people are not assets to be disposed of at our whim. 
each person has significant value to god. he stated, “what you have done to the least of these, you have done unto me.” #godislove #humantrafficking #adoption #abortion #life #abuse #racism #massshootings #violence #metoo #jesus #helpingpeople #endingabuse #children #helpingchildren #love #lovewins

text:
she was under “great psychological pressure” 
chris brown was accused of violently raping a girl earlier this week in paris. he was arrested and detained until police came to the conclusion that there was not enough evidence to charge brown. while the investigation is still ongoing, parisian authorities are having a difficult timee believing the accuser’s story. she claims brown brought her into a secluded area and raped her. she then says she left that room and was raped again in a second room. finally, the accuser claims she left that room and was assaulted a third time. police find it odd that the young lady was sexually abused three separate times and never tried to call for help, raise an alarm, or escape. 
now, according to tmz, the alleged victim’s lawyer frank serfati told the associated press thursday (january 24) that his client “was not pressured physically” into having sex with bown. she insists that “non-consensual sex” allegedly took place though, and that she was under “great psychological pressure” during the interaction. serfati continued on to claim brown “cornered her in a room that was locked” and that “there were forced sexual relations” with “only with men, older men, men who you imagine to be buff.” brown’s bodyguard was also detained and released in connection with the alleged assault. 
meanwhile, chris is maintaining his innocence. he has has now hit the woman with a defamation lawsuit and is putting his innocence on the forefront, quite literally, with new merchandise. in a since-deleted instagram post, chris wrote “this bitch lyin” in his caption and he’s now taken those three words and plastered them on some t-shirts. according to the blast the original term was coined when chris was accused of assaulting model baylee curran back in 2016 and now he’s found another way to bring it back to light again. 
the shirts are being sold online through chris’ black pyramid clothing line, going for $38 a piece. peep the details in the full story at www.itskenbarbie.com what do you guys think? #chrisbrown #chrisbrownofficial #chrisbrownworld #chrisbrownfans #thisbitchlyin #metoo #chrisbrownart #breezy #chrisbreezy #teambreezy #undecided

text:
this reminds me: when we were living in ca, and the boys were 4 and 5, we had a neighbor friend named ethan. ethan was zen, reasonable and kind, this gentle vietnamese little buddha of a guy. i would always offer ethan food and more food and he would politely decline. when i kept asking, he would say so wisely: “maggie, no means no.” and i would just love it(without knowing why). and i would repeat it and still chide him to eat more than he wanted, just so i could hear him say it again.
but see, when you grow up surrounded by people who do not listen when you say no….who pretend you did not say it or attack you for saying it, you do not learn about the boundary of no. so, tiny little ethan was my first model of healthy boundaries via the direct statement of “no”. no is a complete sentence and it is not mean, or a crime.
give it a try. you are welcome. now, i am your life coach.

text:
por primera vez recopiladas en un libro, todas las tiras «feministas» de mafalda.

mafalda, la irreverente niña que ha deleitado a generaciones con su visión humorística del mundo en que vivimos, es una de las más ilustres feministas de nuestra época.

cincuenta años después de su nacimiento, cuando movimientos como time's up o #metoo han dado eco a mujeres de todo el mundo y la lucha por los derechos de las mujeres está más que nunca en el candelero, su lectura del mundo sigue en plena vigencia. las viñetas del genial quino adquieren hoy una fuerza extraordinaria y nos ayudan a tomar conciencia del camino recorrido y por recorrer para conseguir la igualdad de género.

las viñetas recogidas en este volumen dan buena cuenta del carácter feminista de esta niña que a sus seis años reinvindica la curiosidad, la educación, el espíritu crítico y el papel de la mujer en el mundo, y que no está dispuesta a convertirse en un ama de casa de clase media dedicada a los quehaceres domésticos.

la crítica dice:
«por todas esas dudas que genera sobre mí misma, mafalda sigue siendo una biblia. el más honesto de todos los libros sagrados. el que debemos mostrar a los niños nada más empiecen a leer.»
luna miguel, el diario

text:
swipe left>>>>> it's not just fun and games!
video games are a favorite past time for many young people. in fact, we often hear parents talk about going to bed and allowing their kids to stay up till the wee hours of the morning playing video games because they think there is inherent safety in them simply being in the house. well that might have been true with the video games from years ago, but nowadays, a video game console is the equivalent of a party line with built in tracking capabilities! your kids can literally be contacted by someone on the other side of the world or across the street. and, you'll never know who they're communicating with if you don't take the time to learn about the gaming console's chat features and location services. predators can cozy up to your child through their favorite video game and groom them right under your nose. before you know it, your child is being lured out of your home to go meet the new friend they met in their favorite games' chat room. so while parents may have no interest in their child's video game, keep in mind that video games are the new playground for predators. pay attention....it's not just fun and games anymore! #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #activist #mlk 📸:pixaby

adesso il successo di quella imponente iniziativa di sensibilizzazione, che aveva visto piazza duomo “scaldata” da oltre 1.700 coperte di lana, si è concretizzata con una donazione per migliorare la qualità e le prestazioni delle apparecchiature diagnostiche del centro senologico dell’ospedale maggiore. ieri, 24 gennaio,la presentazione ufficiale del pacchetto di aggiornamento software al centro senologico del maggiore alla presenza di nella faimali, presidente dell’associazione la doppia elica, cecilia d’aloia, responsabile del centro senologico e antonino musolino, responsabile della breast unit interaziendale, insieme a girolamo crisi, direttore del dipartimento diagnostico e massimo fabi, direttore generale dell’azienda ospedaliero-universitaria di parma.
info👉🏻: http://www.parmatoday.it/salute/centro-senologico-con-le-donazioni-della-doppia-elica-acquistati-un-software-e-una-workstation.html

text:
being alone on this travel has been a gift.  a scary, wonderful gift. i can no longer follow anything other than my gut, who has alerted me to so much inauthenticity and helped me dodge more loss. when the switch comes on and there is light in our darkness, we then live in tension waiting to change. we fear becoming fearless. we become weak thinking of how strong we are. we fumble and doubt our own sacred knowing...
.
.
i am afraid. i am afraid of becoming whole because my life was built to sanctify how weak and worthless i have felt. i had everything in place to master a great appearance, and stumble through the authentic hunger for connection, being known, and being loved.
.
i am afraid that my old life can not sustain the strength that my new self demands to express. i am afraid that the life i planned out, will cease to exist, because i am listening to my healing heart and it is leading me to more healing, health and sacred care.
.
i am afraid that one more day passes and i do not engage with my true self and celebrate that every waking pain i have known has been a gift, and that gift has lead me to a place of knowing myself and finding myself to be enough, just as i am.
.
so...my fear subsides. and i continue to move forward trusting that we are all fearfully and wonderfully made....no matter where you are....what you are fighting for...i hope this is your truth today❤️
.
.

.

text:
it’s fearless friday!  this pic is really old yet i keep it propped up by my desk as a reminder that i can do things even if they’re scary.
.
this pic was taken in ixtapa right after i went parasailing.  i had been watching others do it for a few days and wanted to try it because it looked really cool, but i hesitated because it also looked scary.  i would have to trust the boat driver to not take me too far out, i’d have to trust that my landing would be safe, i’d have to trust that there wouldn’t be any sharks when i landed....i remember waiting in line and almost left the line a few times.  i was scared.  this was something new to me, it was unknown, and it was something i would have no control over once i was in the air.
.
i loved it!!! the view was breathtaking.  i felt free.  it was relaxing and exhilarating at the same time.  i didn’t want my time in the air to end.  i was sooo glad i stayed in line and waited my turn.  i was so glad i didn’t let my fears take over and get the best of me.  how disappointing it would have been to have missed this experience.
.
when i’m stepping in the unknown, trying something new, needing to trust myself or others, not being able to control a situation and needing to go with the flow, i look at this picture and remember i can do it, i can trust myself and my intuition, i don’t need to have the control or know the outcome in advance, and that sometimes things we really want are a little scary.
.
take a moment today to think about what fear is holding you back.  how can you move forward and not let your fear(s) set you back?  have a great day - it’s friday! 💜

this pic was taken in ixtapa right after i went parasailing.  i had been watching others do it for a few days and wanted to try it because it looked really cool, but i hesitated because it also looked scary.  i would have to trust the boat driver to not take me too far out, i’d have to trust that my landing would be safe, i’d have to trust that there wouldn’t be any sharks when i landed....i remember waiting in line and almost left the line a few times.  i was scared.  this was something new to me, it was unknown, and it was something i would have no control over once i was in the air.
.
i loved it!!! the view was breathtaking.  i felt free.  it was relaxing and exhilarating at the same time.  i didn’t want my time in the air to end.  i was sooo glad i stayed in line and waited my turn.  i was so glad i didn’t let my fears take over and get the best of me.  how disappointing it would have been to have missed this experience.
.
when i’m stepping in the unknown, trying something new, needing to trust myself or others, not being able to control a situation and needing to go with the flow, i look at this picture and remember i can do it, i can trust myself and my intuition, i don’t need to have the control or know the outcome in advance, and that sometimes things we really want are a little scary.
.
take a moment today to think about what fear is holding you back.  how can you move forward and not let your fear(s) set you back?  have a great day - it’s friday! 💜

text:
the first ever black male summit @carnegiemellon is happening next weekend, starting with a keynote lecture from dr. derrick brooms on friday feb 1, and a daylong summit on saturday feb 2.

the summit will feature workshops and panel discussions led by black male cmu students and staff and clinical professionals, including: black manhood 101, black mental health, black men and #metoo, and black male sense of belonging at cmu. this event will serve as the founding weekend of a black male initiative and annual summit.

register now: tinyurl.com/cmu-bms-register

all summit events will be held in the cohon university center and are open to everyone at cmu. breakfast and lunch will be served the day of the summit. 
the keynote lecture is open to the general public and will be followed by a networking reception in the center for student diversity and inclusion.

for questions about the summit and how to get involved in the initiative, email kevin jarbo (kjarbo@cmu.edu)

one in three women experience violence in their lifetime, across all social status, class, race, country or age group. for many of them, the #metoo moment hasn’t come yet, because speaking out can have fatal consequences, and survival is a long and complicated journey.⠀
*a un study of 10,000 men in asia and the pacific, released in 2013, found that overall nearly half of those men interviewed reported using physical and/or sexual violence against a female partner, ranging from 26 percent to 80 percent across the sites studied.  nearly a quarter of men interviewed reported perpetrating rape against a woman or girl, ranging from 10 percent to 62 percent across the sites. #gillette #metoo #hearmetoo #planet5050

un mouvement qui a commencé en octobre 2017, où deux grands journaux new york times et le new yorker, faisaient éclater l’affaire weistein, nom d’un grand producteur de cinéma américain. des actrices violées, humiliées et et manipulées. un mouvement qui s’est étendu et à permis aux femmes de libérer leurs paroles. 
ce livre reprend également les humiliations faites aux femmes dans les publicités, les films, et la banalisation du viol. depuis notre tendre enfance, en nous apprend à ne pas parler aux inconnus, de ne pas rentrer tard ou du moins jamais seule arrivée la tombée de la nuit ( dixit le petit chaperon rouge) 
ce mouvement né en amérique, arrive en france depuis 2018 avec #balancetonporc qui met en lumière le quotidien des femmes françaises, face aux harcèlements de rues. 
bref. un livre que je vous conseil.

text:
yes, our editors belonged to the over two million readers who loved kristen roupenian‘s short story „cat person“ about a complicated and disturbing dating situation in the age of #metoo; 2017 published by @newyorkermag; the author got instantly famous and about a year later we can’t wait to read her recently published collection of short stories „you know you want this“ @simonandschuster;

auch auf deutsch sind die kurzgeschichten mit präzisen, teils bitterkomischen und verstörenden beobachtungen von beziehungen, ob zwischen frauen und männern, vermeintlichen freunden oder kindern, gerade erschienen - übersetzt von dem fantastischen team @zoras_daughter und @friederikeschilbach; jetzt müssen die salon-kollegeninnen sich nur noch einigen, wer den band mit ins wochenende nehmen darf. ☕️📘#blumenbar @aufbau_verlag #freitagsbuchtipp #salonlit #catpersonstorys #kristenroupenian #bookstagram #instabook #bücherliebe

text:
forgiveness is a word that can cause a guttural-defense reaction,
especially for those that have been mistreated or wronged
there are many reasons why a woman would be resistant to embrace and forgive her brothers,
and even to unite with her masculine-self within
and there are many reasons why a man would be hesitant to trust and open to his sisters,
and even to unite with his feminine-self within 
but,
forgiveness itself is something beautiful.
forgiveness is the ability to hold compassion for another soul,
to see the divinity in their being
to acknowledge the beat of their heart
to recognize that they were a baby once, just like you
and they will grow old someday, just like you
forgiveness is to humanize that which we have demonized
it is to face beings that have been cast as monsters,
and to simply see their being-ness within,
it is to acknowledge the untouchable innocence of their soul-spark 
please hear and digest:
forgiveness is entirely different from justification,
as it is about the being and not about their action(s)
forgiveness does not justify abuse, rape, cruelty, bullying, degradation, objectification, injustice, or any toxic behavior
forgiveness for a being and protest/rage towards their actions can unequivocally coexist
we can acknowledge the never-lost innocence of an individual’s soul,
while deeming their human action as guilty 
grant yourself the gift of coexisting contradiction
know that you can despise an action and simultaneously forgive a being 
forgiveness is a decision based in energetic shift
and because this shift takes place in the soul realm,
forgiveness does not always need to be reflected in human word or action
it is more than enough that forgiveness be demonstrated by a shift in your own heart space,
and forgiveness does not need to be proven by giving your time to abusers, staying in dangerous or triggering situations, or through any other external words, commitments or behaviors ✨✨✨✨ my theme word of 2019 is forgiveness, is ho’oponopono. on feb 5th i’m speaking at a @projectfword event that explores the ways forgiveness may belongs in the #metoo movement, according to survivors. more details to come 💚

text:
this week i’ve been reflecting on my role as a researcher. i identify as a woman. i identify as an intersectional feminist. i identify, and have reclaimed the word, as a fat woman.(but that’s another post for another time.) the thing is i have been all too aware of this while researching. almost daily i’m talking to men about two very touchy subjects - masculinity and mental health.

with gender power dynamics i undoubtedly influence their answers - they may not want to offend me and likewise, they may be more open with me as a woman. either way i’ve worked hard to be a researcher first, and a woman second.

my first mistake was separating the two. my second was putting my gender in the backseat.

the longer i do this, the more important i believe the female perspective is. from mothers raising boys to teenage girls having their first relationship. we shape men and men shape us.

when i first spoke to my tutor about being an intersectional feminist researcher (i know it’s a mouthful) she told me to find others. i couldn’t. it made me uncertain.

now i’m certain. so i’m thinking of collecting women’s stories about men’s mental health too. what do you think? is that a good idea?

happy friday! 🚐💨🐶☀️
*
*
*
*
*
*

text_retweet:
#repost @wageforwork ・・・
invitation to biennial artists: use wagency to withhold content in support of whitney staff

this fee request is an example of what withholding content from the 2019 whitney biennial would look like using wagency. artists may include any message they like, but the request will appear to the recipient as it does below. fee requests are sent to recipients from w.a.g.e. on behalf of wagents. it reads:

dear adam d. weinberg, scott rothkopf, and the leadership of the whitney museum, 
please find the fee request for my participation in the 2019 whitney biennial below. the total cost of my labor has been calculated according to w.a.g.e.’s minimum standards of compensation. 
my participation in the exhibition is also contingent upon the fulfillment by leadership of the demands made by whitney staff as detailed below and quoted directly from an internal letter sent to you on november 26, 2018. they are as follows: •​for leadership to convey our concerns to the board, including that they consider asking for warren kanders’ resignation.
•​a public statement from the whitney in response to the hyperallergic article
•​a museum wide staff forum for employees to discuss this and other issues, and related policies moving forward
•​the development and distribution of a clear policy around trustee participation.
(nb: here, we intend to clarify what qualifies or disqualifies a wealthy philanthropic individual for the board. is there a moral line? if so, what is that line? if this was an instance of a #metoo scandal, would we call for resignation? if this was an instance of overt racism, would we call for resignation? we believe the line should be that we not be afflicted with any board member whose work or actions are at odds with the museum’s mission.) i add to these demands that leadership establish a reasonable timeline for their fulfillment. 
thank you for your consideration, i look forward to working with you. 
signed,
wagent x

text:
where are all of my warrior friends? 🙋🏻‍♀️
strength isn’t just physical. 
it’s emotional too💪🏼
this ole journey called life can be filled with twists and turns that leave you feeling weak, can’t it?😐
it can feel as if you’ve been zapped of everything you’ve got. 
knowing you are on the right path will give you the energy to go just “one more lap” 🏃‍♀️ just one more lap is all you need to focus on. 
don’t think about tomorrow or its troubles. focus on today. your purpose. your lane. your “lap”. you’ve got this my friend 👊🏼
#slayonslayer 🤺

🔹
kom förbi och prata jämställdhetsarbete med oss!
trevlig helg!🥰

text:
«die rebellion von bailey davis war nicht nur eine rebellion gegen die
ambivalenten erwartungen an eine cheerleaderin, jene kunstfigur, die zwischen playmate und jungfrau maria pendelt, nicht nur eine reaktion also auf ein patriarchal definiertes frauenbild und eine sexistische kultur. es war auch eine rebellion gegen eine kommerzielle aneignung des weiblichen körpers: die amerikanischen footballteams sind konzerne mit milliardenumsätzen, und die cheerleaderinnen sind ein kleines, aber wichtiges element, das wenig kosten und keinen ärger bereiten soll.» christof gertsch und mikael krogerus haben bailey davis getroffen, die sich gegen sexistische diskriminierungen in der national football league aufgelehnt hat und damit von der cheerleaderin zur #metoo-kämpferin wurde. foto zum artikel: william widmer @misterwidmer #tagimagi #dasmagazin #christofgertsch #mikaelkrogerus #baileydavis #sexismus #nationalfootballleague #cheerleading #cheerleader #reporting #swissjournalism @christof_gertsch

words for the world:
me too part 5. 
a series. .
.
.
parties and fake friends. .
.
this was all fun and games,
and you are acting 
just the same as me.
why is it that only i 
am being told 
i am a dramatic whore?
are you not sleeping with
3 different men and 
two of which
you are tempting to 
be unfaithful.
so why am i 
the uselss whore?
how could you tell me 
in one breath that 
i am strong and 
you admire me,
then turn around and 
throw me under fire 
so no one notices you
and all that you do. 
you are weak. 
you always were. 
i just wish i caught that
before i let your words stick
to my heart. -mahriyah willow

repost from @books_by_marie using @repostregramapp - skammen är inte din av anicia sundström eriksson

en bok på dikt och prosa där författaren blottar sina upplevelser, sin oro, sin längtan, sin förtvivlan - men också hur hon återvinner sitt självförtroende.

i boken tar författaren upp sina tankar om hur hon utnyttjats sexuellt. att bli förövad möjligheten att välja, förlora makten över sin kropp, att kunna säga nej! 
hon beskriver också hur hennes pappa går bort i cancer. att hon inte är beredd, inte får ta farväl, inte får hjälp att bearbeta sina känslor. 
allt som drabbar författaren ger ett ackumulerat känslomässig kaos som skapar psykisk ohälsa. detta kaos skapas av yttre faktorer - och drabbar författaren som inte har en chans att värja sig. 
boken handlar också om vägen tillbaka till bättre mående. om tron på kärleken och att våga närvara i positiva känslor. 
tack för att du delar med dig @aniciaeriksson och tack för #recex ! 🙏🏻

text:
meet our sister - petra de sutter (@pdsutter)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
petra de sutter, 55, is a professor of gynaecology, a politician and the head of the reproductive medicine department at ghent university hospital in belgium. woman with a transgender past and a member of belgian senate, she’s also running as the european greens candidate for the 2019 elections. among other struggles, her engagement for reproductive rights or migrations issues makes her “an incredibly inspiring person" - says our journalist, louise culot.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
photo by mélanie wenger (@_melaniewenger_pictures)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#sistersofeurope #feminism #metoo #europe #lgbtq #petradesutter #reproductiverights

text:
step 7 of our #16stepprogram - on how boys and men can step up and take action for #metoo.

know that consent is complicated and make sure you have it.

consent isn’t a mere “yes” or “no” in any given situation. think about the many situations where consent may be implied but you are not sure since no two situations are the same. 
stop. think. ask. listen. analyse. consent is complicated like all human behaviour. create an open space with your partner/s to be able to comfortably have a dialogue. do not make assumptions on the other person’s behalf.

in collaboration with @thepixelproject
.

text:
taking this #tbt post way back to thursday august 31, 1899! one great aspect to doing demo work on old new england homes is the gems we sometimes find in the walls. apparently mr. breckenridge was ‘no gentleman’ and a ‘liar’ among other things to miss pollard who apparently was the cause of the duel.. front page news 120 years ago! the wood stick with ‘manchester mass’ written on it was about 100 years before ‘by-the-sea’ was officially added to the town name. this piece was used to sister-up another piece of framing. very cool discovery! •
honest craftsmanship •

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text: movies watched in 2019. revisited black swan. it’s a film that in a post #metoo world gives me the ickiest vibes, and for all its technical bravura and well crafted, pressure-cooker atmosphere, i cannot help but feel very uncomfortable about how much of the internalised misogyny that permeates nina’s psychology is intentional commentary or the unconscious purging of aronofsky’s own issues with women. nevertheless, nina is a character who has always resonated with me; her desire for perfection, fear of failure, utter craving for approval and the lack of self love that these things all stem from. i cannot help but feel a personal connection with her in some twisted way.

text:
**warning: this a very long, very personal, and very emotionally charged post** i usually don't share my opinion about abortion because people are so quick to anger and judgement without even listening/thinking these days..but with all the posts i've been reading lately i can't hold it in anymore. let me make it clear that i do not personally believe in abortion. but as a result of my own personal experiences, i cannot judge another woman for her personal choice. 
i remember just like it was yesterday. running out of an unfamiliar building. running down a street that i'd never been down before. no shoes. no phone. turning into a building with a light on and pounding on the window, with tears streaming down my face, until someone finally opened the door. i was so scared, paranoid, hurt, ashamed.. and then angry.. and then empty and depressed. i was lucky enough not to have gotten pregnant. but it was hard enough as it was. 
so instead of just voicing our opinions against women who make the decision to have an abortion, how about we raise our voices in support of other programs?! more programs to support adoption over abortion. more programs and support groups for women who need mental and emotional support during and after their pregnancy.  people say, "just give it up for adoption" like that will solve everything. no matter what they choose, adoption or abortion, they're still left with what happened to them long after.
 and it's not just victims of sexual assault that need support. it could be young women who are scared and they may not have the support of family or a spouse/partner. or there could be other complications that lead them to feel like they need to abort their pregnancy. 
again, i'm not saying i support abortion. but i do believe that we should be more empathetic and proactive in supporting these women instead of just passing judgment. ❤
#believewomen #metoo #yesallwomen

text:
i’ve heard too many stories from my students, friends, clients, past lovers of being abused, raped, & ultimately disrespected in every sense of the word by a man not only a man but a man of color. it hurts because i’ve grown to realize how truly common it is, especially in our own community. i personally know the disrespectful men and the queens who’ve been disrespected. i’m not all with the #metoo movement but a true paradigm shift is needed. we need to grow and appreciate the 2nd self of god. i’m with a movement that respects women because too much disrespect has been tolerated for too long. respect the queen 🖤🙏🏾

text:
i wonder if we are going to look back on the awful hateful way we engage in mouth battles on the internet and wish we would have spent our time differently. 
no one is going to change the mind of a trump supporter. just like no one will ever convince someone to support trump. 
disrespecting the flag versus kneeling against racism. innocent until proven guilty versus the #metoo movement. a razor ad. a questionable smirk. today, my feed is loaded with hateful awful us against them language because some believe they know what’s best when it comes to babies and bodies. 
everything is a thing. it’s exhausting. 
i’m done with the mouth battles. 
i could be doing awesome shit but instead i’m reading threads loaded with people being assholes to each other. 
figuring out how to get my phone to stop autocorrecting “ducking” would spark more joy than comments in any thread i’ve read this week. 
i’m going to do what i need to do to support what aligns with my belief system. i’m just going to kick it old school. 
i’ll argue with people across the table about why they are wrong. like the good ole days. you know, back when things would get heated and someone storms out super pissed but then stomps back in to add one more thing. and someone else yells everybody calm down which is the least calming thing to say in that moment. 
but i’m done engaging in any us against them rhetoric. mouth battles on the internet will not change anyone’s mind. 
it just doesn’t ducking work...😜 #seewhatididthere  #instagood #love #lovewins #stop #justdont #cantwealljustgetalong #dontbeanasshole #tiredaf #itsgoingtobeokay  #maybe #whoknows #kindness

text:
quanada cites power of #metoo following ernst confession
#
quanada cites power of #metoo following ernst confessionquincy, ill. — the highest ranking female republican in the senate said thursday she was mentally and physically abused by her ex-husband.senator joni ernst shared she was forced to reveal details of her private pain -- after her divorce documents became public.the iowa republican has also revealed she's a rape survivor.khqa met with the quincy area network against domestic abuse also known as quanada today.executive director megan duesterhaus said the senator's experience is one that many women face.she says the metoo movement shows power in numbers and the perversity of domestic abuse.“what we just keep seeing is that sexual violence is everywhere and it doesn't discriminate. it happens to people from all walks of life. if it could happen to a well-known legislator, it could happen to your second-grade teacher,” duesterhaus said.duesterhaus stresses that sharing your story is not for everyone and to come forward when you're ready. original article source...

quanada cites power of  following ernst confessionquincy, ill. — the highest ranking female republican in the senate said thursday she was mentally and physically abused by her ex-husband.senator joni ernst shared she was forced to reveal details of her private pain -- after her divorce documents became public.the iowa republican has also revealed she's a rape survivor.khqa met with the quincy area network against domestic abuse also known as quanada today.executive director megan duesterhaus said the senator's experience is one that many women face.she says the metoo movement shows power in numbers and the perversity of domestic abuse.“what we just keep seeing is that sexual violence is everywhere and it does not discriminate. it happens to people from all walks of life. if it could happen to a well-known legislator, it could happen to your second-grade teacher,” duesterhaus said.duesterhaus stresses that sharing your story is not for everyone and to come forward when you are ready. original aicle source...

“childhood trauma is relational trauma... you can't heal relational trauma by yourself. it has to be healed in relationships.” - joyelle brandt.

relational trauma requires relational repair. repeatedly in the testimony of survivors there comes a moment when a sense of connection is restored by another person's unaffected display of generosity. something in themselves that the victims believed to be irretrievably destroyed - faith, decency, courage - is reawakened by an example of common altruism. mirrored in the actions of others or someone, the survivor recognizes and reclaims a lost part of herself or himself.

text:
jag tänkte i början att han sa att jag gjorde fel, hade fel kläder och sa fel saker för att han ville hjälpa mig. så jag kunde göra rätt. att han kanske var lite hård, men att det var tough love. jag var 21 år. vad visste jag om livet, om nånting? jag tog tacksamt emot guidning. till slut frågade jag honom om allt.
jag hade aldrig haft en pojkvän som gjort så, men jag tänkte att ingen hade heller älskat mig som han. med den där nästan vansinniga glöden.

han hörde av sig väldigt ofta. mina vänner blev irriterade, men jag tänkte att de inte förstår, hur mycket han älskar mig.

han ville att jag slutade på mitt jobb och började jobba på hans istället. när jag tvekade blev han arg, sa att jag inte hade några ambitioner. jag tänkte, att han tror verkligen på mig.

han gillade inte mina vänner eller min familj. sa att de inte var bra för mig. och kanske var det sant. de fanns inte där för mig som han.

han sa att jag började bli tjock, att jag borde träna. ”jag vet att du skulle hata dig själv om du blev tjock”. omtanke.

när det gått så långt att han skrek på mig om jag la besticken fel på köksbordet började jag inse. men då var det för sent. jag var fast. vi bodde ihop. jag hade ingen kontakt med min familj, inte många vänner kvar. han var min chef. jag hade en låg lön, jobbade inte heltid. ”jag tror inte du klarar av det, filippa”.
när hans makt var total tog misshandeln stora proportioner. det var som att leva i en vansinnesvärld. ena dagen snäll, andra dagen ett monster. och så blommor och presenter dagen efter. en muta för att glömma. och jag ville så gärna glömma.

till slut blev det en praktisk kamp. hur skulle jag få tag i en lägenhet, ha råd att leva ensam? samtidigt kämpade jag mot tankarna, att vi hörde ihop, efter allt vi varit med om. att ingen annan skulle orka med mig. vem skulle finnas där för mig, hjälpa mig, om inte han? jag hade ingen.
det var ett fängelse. åt vilket håll jag än vände mig såg jag galler. det fanns ingen väg ut.

att bli fri gick inte på en dag, det hände i etapper. hade jag inte gjort den där intervjun i dn i okt 2017 så vet jag inte. kanske hade jag fortfarande suttit fast. fast i hans kontroll.

för han älskade mig ju så mycket.

text:
oulu on mun lapsuudenkoti. peruskoulua tuli käytyä yhdeksän vuoden aikana kahdessa eri koulussa keskustan sydämessä, jossa molemmissa oppilaita oli kaikista maailman kolkista. monella oli varhaisteineissä kova kiire kasvaa aikuisiksi, ja seksi oli kiinnostava kielletty tabu jonka kanssa flirttailu oli tie aikuisuuteen. päihteet pelas samaa roolia, ja jotta molempien kanssa sai olla tekemisissä piti olla myös tekemisissä täysi-ikäisten kanssa. milloin minäkin viikonloppuna joku ajokortin ja auton omistava hakija (viittaa ihmiseen joka ostaa alaikäisille päihteitä yleensä rahasta) oli meidän seiska, kasi ja ysiluokkalaisten seurassa. asiasta ei pidetty isoa älämölöä, mutta nämä samat hakijat sattuivat aina seurustelemaan jonkun kaveriporukassa olevan tytön kanssa. suurempia selittelemättä välillä pohdittiin sitä, että miten voi kieltäytyä seksistä ilman että poikakaveri jättää. missä menee raja painostamisen ja seksuaalisen väkivallan välillä, ja että miten voi selittää raskauden teini-ikäisenä kun kumppani ei elä murrosikävuosia vaan ajaa bemaria. 
peruskoulun jälkeen olen kouluttautunut ylioppilaaksi, sekä valmistunut vaatetusalan ammattilaiseksi toisessa maakunnassa. kuusitoista ja seitsemäntoista kesäisinä raja alaikäisten ja täysi-ikäisten välillä hälveni lähes olemattomiin. ei ollut ollenkaan poikkeuksellista, että alaikäiset amis ja lukiolaiset seurustelivat täysi-ikäisten kumppaneiden kanssa. kaikkina kouluvuosina kun seksi ja seksuaalisuus tuli yhä olennaisemmaksi, niin lukuisilla tunneilla taottiin päähän miten lisääntyminen tapahtuu. kertaakaan koko 14-vuoden kouluvuosieni aikana ei kuitenkaan yhtä perusteellisesti käsitelty seksuaalista itsemääräämisoikeutta, ja oikeutta sanaan ei. jos sattui ilmoittamaan, että (yleensä pojat) heittää kuminpalasia miehustaan tai muutoin rikkoo seksuaalisen koskemattomuuden rajoja, niin sai mediassa hiljattain huomiota herättäneen rehtorin ajatusten kaltaisia vastauksia. kuitenkin harvoin istuttiin terveystiedon tai biologian tunnilla jossa jakamatonta oikeutta koskemattomuuteen korostettiin sukupuolittuneita pukeutumissääntöjä vahvemmin.  1/3
📷@kinain

манчестерская художественная галерея сняла с экспозиции работу уотерхауса «гилас и нимфы» и попросила аудиторию высказать своё мнение по поводу обнаженного женского тела.
.
на картине изображены обнажённые нимфы, заманивающие красивого молодого человека в смертельную ловушку. но не слишком ли далеко зашла эротическая фантазия представителя викторианской эпохи? не слишком ли она неуместна и даже оскорбительна для современного зрителя?
.

именно с этим вопросом обратилась к посетителям манчестерская галерея, убрав из зала одно из самых известных полотен.
так же работу убрали и из музейного магазина.
.
посетителям предложили написать свое мнение на стикере и наклеить его на стену, где висела картина
.
как пишет «би-би-си», на заявления галереи посетители отреагировали стикерами на стене со словами «феминизм сошел с ума» и «создавайте и показывайте искусство, которое отражает сегодняшние идеологии, наравне со старым. места хватит и для того, и для другого».
.
причём тут феминизм, скажите вы?↘️ куратор отдела современного искусства клэр гэннеуэй позднее добавила в комментарии , что зал, в котором находится полотно уотрехауса, называется «в погоне за красотой», и одна из целей сотрудников манчестерского музея — изменить представления о том, что женское тело является «пассивным объектом мужского потребления» и по-новому взглянуть на картины
.
через неделю картина вернулась на место. позже в пресс-релизе объявили, что это была часть совместного перфоманса с художником сони бойс для ее персональной выставки и сплочения людей.
.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

причём тут феминизм, скажите вы?↘️ куратор отдела современного искусства клэр гэннеуэй позднее добавила в комментарии , что зал, в котором находится полотно уотрехауса, называется «в погоне за красотой», и одна из целей сотрудников манчестерского музея — изменить представления о том, что женское тело является «пассивным объектом мужского потребления» и по-новому взглянуть на картины
.
через неделю картина вернулась на место. позже в пресс-релизе объявили, что это была часть совместного перфоманса с художником сони бойс для ее персональной выставки и сплочения людей.
.

text:
с 16 по 21 января 2019 года горнолыжный курорт «солнечная ☀ долина» в городе миасс (челябинская область) стал «столицей» российского фристайла – на курорте прошли этапы кубка и первенства 🇷🇺 россии по фристайлу в дисциплинах слоуп-стайл, биг-эйр и хаф-пайп.
⠀
в соревнованиях приняли участие более 80 фристайлистов со всей россии: из москвы, санкт-петербурга, краснодарского края, томска, пермского края, красноярского края, республики башкортостан и чувашской республики. 🎿🏂
⠀
спортсмен сшор по зимним видам спорта «мгфсо» москомспорта федор муралев в дисциплине хаф-пайп завоевал золото первенства россии, а также бронзу на этапе кубка россии.😎
⠀

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text: morgen in unserer neuen ausgabe: der maler und filmemacher julian schnabel hat einen guten film über vincent van gogh gedreht. van gogh, ein labiler mensch, ein wahnsinniger gar, ist das prototypische genie der kunstgeschichte. wer sich mit kunst und wahn beschäftigt, landet rasch bei van gogh. schnabels film lohnt sich – das jedenfalls ist unsere schlussfolgerung nach der lektüre des gesprächs von sven michaelsen mit dem regisseur. noch besser jedoch ist, sich künftig viel zeit zu nehmen für die betrachtung von gemälden, man muss dafür nicht einmal ins museum gehen. selbst seerosen auf kochschürzen tun ihre wirkung. ausserdem: die #metoo-bewegung hat die national football league erreicht. dank bailey davis. unsere reporter christof gertsch und mikael krogerus haben die ex-cheerleaderin getroffen, die quasi über nacht zur kämpferin einer bewegung wurde. titelbild: julian baumann (@baumann_julian), werk im hintergrund: julian schnabel, big girl painting, 2013 © 2019, prolitteris, zurich #tagimagi #dasmagazin #julianschnabel #vangogh #vincentvangogh #metoo #baileydavis #reporting #art

book title: #metoo brutus
author: prana natrajan @praneix
format: paperback
.
🔗the book is based on a movement #metoo . it is a movement against sexual harassment and sexual assault.the movement began to spread virally in october 2017 as a hashtag on social media in an attempt to demonstrate the widespread prevalence of sexual assault and harassment, especially in the workplace.
.
🔗the author here tells story of many common women who face abuse in different ways like physically, sexually and mentally.
.
🔗the cover of the book shows an ankle of a girl tied up with a chain which displays an important message. the title of the book is totally related to the book. i found the cover page really very beautiful.
.
🔗the writing style is appreciable and language used is easy to understand.
.
🔗the first in the line is the story is based on hira. she is an intelligent girl. one of her college friend faced acid attack so her parents thought to send her to a different city. but going to a different city will make a change? there is a huge twist.
the story is medium paced but it is full of twists and turns.
the next we have sanya, who has faced many stereotypes as a girl and raped by her own husband. what she will do?
aaliya and many more.
.
🔗the characters potrayed are well developed as you can actually feel the emotions of each and every character or victims.
.
🔗overall, it was a good read.
.
🔗recommendation: yes
.
🔗🌟🌟🌟🌟.5/5

text:
🗞каждый декабрь известный журнал экономист издает специальный выпуск в котором прогнозируются события будушего года. 📰обложка представляет собой сложный комплекс загадочных рисунков. 📊экономист это не просто издание, оно напрямую принадлежит мировой элите, банкирам и английским семьям. одной из таких как ротшильды. 📌издание экономист хорошо осведомлено о повестке дня элиты.

2️⃣0️⃣1️⃣9️⃣
итак, мир в 2019 году - это очередная кабаллистическая шифто пиктограмма прогноза дома ротшильдов. необходимо заметить что это уже 33-й выпуск (нумерологический факт).
🔴обложка выполнена в стиле леонардо да винчи, зеркальное письмо, перевернутые символы. 🔴в центре расположен витрувианский человек, эскиз да винчи.
современный человек 2019 года, носит очки ночного видения, в руках он держит лист конопли, бейсбольный мяч и смартфон.
все эти вещи используются что бы отвлечь человека, фармацевтические компании, технологии, и развлечения. 🔴у витрувианского человека на теле расположены две татуировки: одна с кодом днк , вторая со стороны сердца ”me too!” (мы помним что голливудское движение #metoo выявило голивудских моральных уродов, в защиту от сексуальных домогательств). 🔴витрувианский человек держит весы правосудия, на которой в одной чаше 5 человек, сильно перевешивает чаша в которой 4 человека (говорит ли нам это о том что в сша появился новый неоднозначный судья в верховном суде?). 🔴обложка анализирует пропорции головы дональда трампа.
для сравнения оригинальный эскиз расположен напротивтрампа, что говорит нам о том, физиономия американского президента далеко не идеальна. 🔴на другой стороне изображение в.в. путина с надписью «трубопроводы путина». связано ли это с газопроводами в сирии? нордстрим-2 который будет завершен в 2019? тюркстрим который был запущен уже в 2018! 🔴оба президента великих держав смотрят на панду — символ китая.
экономический конфликт между сша и китаем! 🔴немного выше, японская святыня, гора фудзияма.
возможно подписание договора о мире, между россией и японией, на счет курильских островов. 🔴справа от путина нарисован пинокио, нос которого растет когда он начинает лгать! пинокио это сложная массонская аллегория!
👇🏻👇🏻👇🏻👇🏻👇🏻

text:
what if law enforcement talked to people who have been robbed the same way they often treat people who have been sexually assaulted?

a new video written and directed by cynthia kao shows how absurd common responses to sexual assault allegations seem within the context of a robbery.

in the video, two police officers question a man about a laptop stolen from his home and continually suggest that the robbery was his fault — a nod to the victim-blaming so common in sexual assault cases. “flashing your goods for all the world to see? kinda sounds like you were asking for it,” one cop says when the man says his laptop was in front of a window. 
the officers also ask if the victim had been drinking question the “lack of evidence,” and tell the robbed man that filing a report will only cause more trouble. sexual assault survivors commonly hear these questions from police officers, which in turn discourages them from charging their assailants or even reporting the assault in the first place.

we wouldn’t blame someone for becoming a laptop-theft victim — don’t assault survivors deserve the same? - huffington post

#speakout #nomore #timesup #justice #metoo #endsexualassault #stopvictimblaming #supportingsurvivors #whyyoushouldreport

text:
this is a huge huge lesson that over the years i have struggled to learn. i always believed that if i could make other people happy by giving then i would find my own happiness. but oh how the tide has changed when i finally realised that actually i was in charge of my own happiness, that only i could truly make myself happy, and i was on a severe pathway of self destruction. i worked in this place where i always gave, my time, my heart, my energy ect, a place where i considered the people in it my friends and family. people were more than happy to take take take, but when i left only 1 person took the time to actually see how we were doing, and i got to realised that i was just being used again. into this new year i am so glad that i have the few people around that i do, how they are so genuine, and mean the world to me, the true meaning of friendship. i am also grateful for the people i have met, the places i've been, and the lessons that i have been able to learn along the way, because without them i wouldn't be the person i am today, that walked through hell and extinguished the flames, have the peace i hold within, the happiness that i have learned to create myself, and the beauty of true friendship.
❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🌈🦄🦋🧘‍♀️🤸‍♀️💪🌻👣🛣️

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
организму человека необходимо регулярно избавляться от накапливающихся шлаков – это помогает сохранить активность клеточных процессов, а значит – продлить молодость. начинать общее очищение следует именно с кишечника. загрязнение кишечника нарушает усвоение минеральных веществ, в нем накапливаются продукты распада, которые отравляют организм, вызывая недомогание, усталость и слабость. после очищения ворсинки кишечника освобождаются, в результате чего улучшается способность всасывания и повышается иммунитет.
очищающий чайный напиток lux выводит шлаки из кишечника, способствует комплексному очищению организма, оказывает легкое мочегонное действие. сочетание растений, обладающих целебным, восстанавливающим и профилактическим действиями активизирует функцию самоочищения организма и восстанавливает работу желудочно-кишечного тракта. солодка в составе чайного напитка улучшает местный иммунитет кишечника, а тмин предотвращает газообразование, поэтому чай хорошо переносится.
для кого?
для тех, кто любит вкусный чай.
для тех, кто заботится о здоровье.
для тех, кому важен состав чая.
для тех, кто хочет заваривать чай в любом месте.
name: Nl - бизнес и здоровье

*
ive got a long way to go - which is kind of exciting. but hot tip: if it, they, she, he, them are not able to meet you in all of your glory; dip. gtfo. leave. because as much as emptiness and solitude can feel vast and intimidating; there's nothing more lonely than the lonliness of not being met by those you are surrounded by. and solitude , as tough as it can feel, is the soil where possibility sprouts and blooms and all that good shit. *
*
*
so: for me, 2019 is about sending all things that don't serve vitality and joy into the trashchute. xo.

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
gop is dead. gop remains dead. and we have killed him. how shall we comfort ourselves, the murderers of all murderers? what was holiest and mightiest of all that the world has yet owned has bled to death under our knives: who will wipe this blood off us? what water is there for us to clean ourselves? what festivals of atonement, what sacred games shall we have to invent? is not the greatness of this deed too great for us? must we ourselves not become gods simply to appear worthy of it?

howlindsey doody

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
is there room for forgiveness and redemption in the #metoo era?
#
is there room for forgiveness and redemption in the #metoo era? can society forgive the men caught up in the #metoo movement? is it even our place to decide? doug mataconis · thursday, january 24, 2019 · 24 comments in a column at bloomberg, tyler cowen wonders if there’s room for second chances in the #metoo era: the longer that the #metoo movement continues, the more important these questions will become: when should offenders be rehabilitated, allowed to resume their careers, and readmitted to polite society? whether we like it or not, as the list of wrongdoers grows, questions of forgiveness will begin to outnumber questions of punishment. the thing is, questions of forgiveness are never entirely easy. much christian doctrine, and especially catholicism, emphasizes the value of confession, forgiveness and redemption. thus it is not hard to convince many americans that sinners should be given a second chance. this impulse occasionally finds its way into policy; just last month, a prison-reform bill became law, reflecting notions that criminals can indeed be rehabilitated. in her book “the up side of down,” washington post columnist megan mcardle stresses how many features of american life, including bankruptcy law and startup culture, depend on second,…

text:
one of my patients, who is in her late 70s, has written an article on my website about why she is still taking hrt. 
she states “there has been so much media coverage about #metoo but now we must campaign for ‘renewed life in middle age’”.
the full article can be read here - https://www.menopausedoctor.co.uk/menopause/to-take-or-not-to-take-that-is-the-question
all the current menopause guidelines are clear that women can take hrt for as long as the benefits outweigh any risks. there is no upper age limit nor maximum length of time for taking hrt. 
i personally will never stop taking my hrt as i worry about osteoporosis and stopping hrt will then increase my risk of osteoporosis. 
taking hrt needs to be an individualised choice which is often easier to make when women are given correct, evidence based and non-biased information. 
#menopause #womenshealth #hormones #hrt #empoweringwomen #knowledgeispower #guidelines

text:
🎁バレンタインdeけんぽうカフェ🎁 ‼️要望にお応えして、金・土曜開催いたしましたぁ！
今回もいろんな話題が飛び出しましたよ。
しかも、マジですか？って話だらけ！ ❤️1月のテーマは 「21条 表現の自由」 ●今の憲法：考えていることを外に発表することは自由。それについて検閲してはダメ。人の手紙や電話やメールも見てはダメ。
→国から介入されず、制約なく表現できる！
●自民党改憲案：基本、発表してもいいけど、内容が公益および公の秩序を害するものは禁止。その判断は、政府が行う。検閲はしてはならないけど、警察の盗聴は広範囲で立会なしでしてもいい(2016年 盗聴法)
→政府がダメだと判断すれば、デモや集会、コミケ！こうした勉強会もできなくなるの？？？ ❤️知ると怖いよ『緊急事態条項』自民党改憲で新しく作られることになる98条と99条
●緊急事態の宣言 98条
緊急事態の対象に制限なし 政府の判断で宣言できる
→独裁国家？
●緊急事態の宣言の効果
緊急事態の宣言をすれば、政府が好きなように政令が作れる。期間なし。歯止めなし。従わないと処罰あり。議員の任期や選挙期日の特例も作れる。
→国民を守る憲法がそもそもなくなる？ ❤️そもそも、基本的人権って何？基本的人権って細かく決められているんだって。
まず大きく4つ
①自由権 ②社会権 ③参政権 ④受益権
今回の表現の自由は①自由権の中のさらに３つ
①精神的自由 ②経済的自由 ③身体的自由
その①精神的自由の中に
①思想・良心の自由 ②信教の自由 ③表現の自由 ④学問の自由と、なるそうです。🤔うーん、考えたことなかった！ ❤️最新ニュース  あなたは、どう思う？ ・tカード情報令状なく操作に提供、当局は保秘
・スマホゲームで位置把握か？
・教育勅語復権へじわり「今日にも通用」下村氏、局長答弁を変更か
・政府、デマ拡散防止へ本格対策 選挙や災害時、法制化は見送り
・首相サンゴ移植発言 フェイク発信許されない
・厚労省 賃金や労働時間 不適切な手法で調査 15年前からか
・総務省 「消費動向指数」でもデータ誤り 公表見送り修正
・辺野古工事で防衛省 県に無断で土砂割合変更 ❤️カフェで出た井戸端会議 驚きの話！
参加者さん；偉い人達(教育改革国民会議第一分科会)でそれぞれの委員発言の概要、凄いんでみてみて！
早速、大人や行政が主体となって家庭・学校・地域で取り組むべきことと載ったプリントを皆でみると・・・
↓↓↓
家庭(保護者)
⚫︎「子供を厳しく「飼い馴らす」必要があることを国民にアピールして覚悟してもらう」
⚫︎「ここで時代が終わった」「変わらないと日本が滅びる」というようなことをアナウンスし、ショック療法を行う
⚫︎団地、マンションに「床の間」を作る

皆さん；これって、ほんとの話？？大丈夫なのこれ？

でも、この内容は2016年に更新されており平成１２年、教育改革国民会議第１分科会（第４回）『一人一人が取り組む人間性教育の具体策（委員発言の概要）』なる資料で見られます。http://www.kantei.go.jp/jp/kyouiku/1bunkakai/dai4/1-4siryou1.html
日本の教育のトップの皆さまはこう考えておられるんですね。 ●参加者さん；nhk総合 「未来塾」で憲法についてやってたよ
速攻でネット検索した私たち♡
→20日（日）午前10時05分から放送の「未来塾」のテーマは「憲法」
作家・高橋源一郎さんを講師に迎え、塾生たちが自分ならではの憲法を作ってしまおうという企画。
参加者たちでも作ってみようかと声が出ましたが、キビシー！塾生さんの前文を読んでみた後、現憲法の前文を読みましたよ。現憲法の前文やっぱいいねーとの感想の参加者たちでした。 ❤️そんなこんなで、1月に金土開催が好評につき
2月も二回開催することになりました！
2月は16日と22日です！
お待ちしていまーす！

#埼玉 #浦和 #21条 #表現の自由
#metoo #夫婦別姓 #浦和パルコ #基本的人権 #コミケ

でも、この内容は2016年に更新されており平成１２年、教育改革国民会議第１分科会（第４回）『一人一人が取り組む人間性教育の具体策（委員発言の概要）』なる資料で見られます。http://www.kantei.go.jp/jp/kyouiku/1bunkakai/dai4/1-4siryou1.html
日本の教育のトップの皆さまはこう考えておられるんですね。 ●参加者さん；nhk総合 「未来塾」で憲法についてやってたよ
速攻でネット検索した私たち♡
→20日（日）午前10時05分から放送の「未来塾」のテーマは「憲法」
作家・高橋源一郎さんを講師に迎え、塾生たちが自分ならではの憲法を作ってしまおうという企画。
参加者たちでも作ってみようかと声が出ましたが、キビシー！塾生さんの前文を読んでみた後、現憲法の前文を読みましたよ。現憲法の前文やっぱいいねーとの感想の参加者たちでした。 ❤️そんなこんなで、1月に金土開催が好評につき
2月も二回開催することになりました！
2月は16日と22日です！
お待ちしていまーす！

#metoo #夫婦別姓 #浦和パルコ #基本的人権 #コミケ

今回もいろんな話題が飛び出しましたよ。
しかも、マジですか？って話だらけ！ ❤️1月のテーマは 「21条 表現の自由」 ●今の憲法：考えていることを外に発表することは自由。それについて検閲してはダメ。人の手紙や電話やメールも見てはダメ。
→国から介入されず、制約なく表現できる！
●自民党改憲案：基本、発表してもいいけど、内容が公益および公の秩序を害するものは禁止。その判断は、政府が行う。検閲はしてはならないけど、警察の盗聴は広範囲で立会なしでしてもいい(2016年 盗聴法)
→政府がダメだと判断すれば、デモや集会、コミケ！こうした勉強会もできなくなるの？？？ ❤️知ると怖いよ『緊急事態条項』自民党改憲で新しく作られることになる98条と99条
●緊急事態の宣言 98条
緊急事態の対象に制限なし 政府の判断で宣言できる
→独裁国家？
●緊急事態の宣言の効果
緊急事態の宣言をすれば、政府が好きなように政令が作れる。期間なし。歯止めなし。従わないと処罰あり。議員の任期や選挙期日の特例も作れる。
→国民を守る憲法がそもそもなくなる？ ❤️そもそも、基本的人権って何？基本的人権って細かく決められているんだって。
まず大きく4つ
①自由権 ②社会権 ③参政権 ④受益権
今回の表現の自由は①自由権の中のさらに３つ
①精神的自由 ②経済的自由 ③身体的自由

・スマホゲームで位置把握か？
・教育勅語復権へじわり「今日にも通用」下村氏、局長答弁を変更か
・政府、デマ拡散防止へ本格対策 選挙や災害時、法制化は見送り
・首相サンゴ移植発言 フェイク発信許されない
・厚労省 賃金や労働時間 不適切な手法で調査 15年前からか
・総務省 「消費動向指数」でもデータ誤り 公表見送り修正

stem_filter: 🎁バレンタインdeけんぽうカフェ🎁 ‼️要望にお応えして、金・土曜開催いたしましたぁ！ 今回もいろんな話題が飛び出しましたよ。 しかも、マジですか？って話だらけ！ ❤️1月のテーマは 「21条 表現の自由」 ●今の憲法：考えていることを外に発表することは自由。それについて検閲してはダメ。人の手紙や電話やメールも見てはダメ。 →国から介入されず、制約なく表現できる！ ●自民党改憲案：基本、発表してもいいけど、内容が公益および公の秩序を害するものは禁止。その判断は、政府が行う。検閲はしてはならないけど、警察の盗聴は広範囲で立会なしでしてもいい ( 2016年 盗聴法 ) →政府がダメだと判断すれば、デモや集会、コミケ！こうした勉強会もできなくなるの？？？ ❤️知ると怖いよ『緊急事態条項』自民党改憲で新しく作られることになる98条と99条 ●緊急事態の宣言 98条 緊急事態の対象に制限なし 政府の判断で宣言できる →独裁国家？ ●緊急事態の宣言の効果 緊急事態の宣言をすれば、政府が好きなように政令が作れる。期間なし。歯止めなし。従わないと処罰あり。議員の任期や選挙期日の特例も作れる。 →国民を守る憲法がそもそもなくなる？ ❤️そもそも、基本的人権って何？基本的人権って細かく決められているんだって。 まず大きく4つ ①自由権 ②社会権 ③参政権 ④受益権 今回の表現の自由は①自由権の中のさらに３つ ①精神的自由 ②経済的自由 ③身体的自由 その①精神的自由の中に ①思想・良心の自由 ②信教の自由 ③表現の自由 ④学問の自由と、なるそうです。🤔うーん、考えたことなかった！ ❤️最新ニュース あなたは、どう思う？ ・tカード情報令状なく操作に提供、当局は保秘 ・スマホゲームで位置把握か？ ・教育勅語復権へじわり「今日にも通用」下村氏、局長答弁を変更か ・政府、デマ拡散防止へ本格対策 選挙や災害時、法制化は見送り ・首相サンゴ移植発言 フェイク発信許されない ・厚労省 賃金や労働時間 不適切な手法で調査 15年前からか ・総務省 「消費動向指数」でもデータ誤り 公表見送り修正 ・辺野古工事で防衛省 県に無断で土砂割合変更 ❤️カフェで出た井戸端会議 驚きの話！ 参加者さん；偉い人達 ( 教育改革国民会議第一分科会 ) でそれぞれの委員発言の概要、凄いんでみてみて！ 早速、大人や行政が主体となって家庭・学校・地域で取り組むべきことと載ったプリントを皆でみると・・・ ↓↓↓ 家庭 ( 保護者 ) ⚫︎「子供を厳しく「飼い馴らす」必要があることを国民にアピールして覚悟してもらう」 ⚫︎「ここで時代が終わった」「変わらないと日本が滅びる」というようなことをアナウンスし、ショック療法を行う ⚫︎団地、マンションに「床の間」を作る 皆さん；これって、ほんとの話？？大丈夫なのこれ？ でも、この内容は2016年に更新されており平成１２年、教育改革国民会議第１分科会（第４回）『一人一人が取り組む人間性教育の具体策（委員発言の概要）』なる資料で見られます。 日本の教育のトップの皆さまはこう考えておられるんですね。 ●参加者さん；nhk総合 「未来塾」で憲法についてやってたよ 速攻でネット検索した私たち♡ →20日（日）午前10時05分から放送の「未来塾」のテーマは「憲法」 作家・高橋源一郎さんを講師に迎え、塾生たちが自分ならではの憲法を作ってしまおうという企画。 参加者たちでも作ってみようかと声が出ましたが、キビシー！塾生さんの前文を読んでみた後、現憲法の前文を読みましたよ。現憲法の前文やっぱいいねーとの感想の参加者たちでした。 ❤️そんなこんなで、1月に金土開催が好評につき 2月も二回開催することになりました！ 2月は16日と22日です！ お待ちしていまーす！ 現の自由
