text:
join us over a glass of fizz 🥂 and some of victors stunning sharing platters as we chat, dine and laugh, along with like-minded ladies and gents for another club elle event.⠀
⠀
we'll be offering networking with a difference so be sure to bring your business cards along and it may be an idea to organise a sitter! 👶🏼 club elle is an amazing opportunity to donate your toiletries and get involved with our fantastic raffle and of course, all proceeds going to vulnerable women living in refuges. ⠀
we'll have 15-minute phsycic love readings from the queen who is eleanor - £15 per reading. 🔮⠀
andrea crump is the fearless love coach, one of the leading love & relationship coaches in the uk and bbc relationship expert. 💏⠀
andrea is fantastically motivational and will have you and your relationship habits whipped into shape in no time. we’re so happy that she has agreed to be our guest speaker and to help whether married, single or it's complicated. ⠀
you’ll love her! ⠀
we’ll have fab tunes by our fave dj, di of @chickswithdecksuk and amazing raffle prizes. 🎟⠀
did we already mention, get a sitter! 👩‍👧‍👧 victors alderley edge is a stylish restaurant and bar set over 2 floors with an exclusive private dining room- perfect for your special occasion. located in the centre of the village on london road, victors has quickly become one of the main hubs of the village, serving brunch through to dinner daily.⠀
⠀
13/02/2019⠀
12-4pm⠀
@victors_restaurants ⠀
london road, alderley edge sk9 7dz, uk⠀

text:
“healing begins through confession. if god can transform your life in 2 years imagine what he can do in a lifetime.”- @desiraeramirezz •
•
•
wow this was the first time i ever publicly shared my testimony in 2017. even then, i resisted sharing a lot.
i was 7 months out from my assault & i was still confused & trying my hardest to just heal at my own pace and not at anyone else’s. i was heavily seeing my therapist 2-3x a week & very much involved in my church. 
it was all i had.
it was all i knew.
it was the only lifelines i had at the time.
•
•
•
this video was released at my former church & it was so hard to film. i was trembling & crying hard when i watched this back on the big stage. i was struggling so much  with the desirae i was listening to in the video. let alone the one i was becoming sitting in the seats. •
•
•
to be honest, i still cry & get shaken up when i share my story because of how graphic & traumatizing it is ...... but i share it with so much courage now. ✊🏼 because it is my story.
it is my healing.
it is my faith.
it is my journey.
this is what courage looked like then.
what you see today is what bravery looks like now 🥰

this video resurfaced today on my facebook & as i rewatched it i cannot begin to express how proud i am of who i am becoming 🙌🏽🙏🏽 [full video] available in the link in the bio ☝🏽
.
.
.
.

text:
good morning long beach! it’s a new day and there are new hopes and dreams in my heart.

after a few weeks without my cell service, i’m feeling reflective. i was able to negotiate with my cell provider to remove my abusive ex’s cell phone charge from my phone line. i’m feeling thankful for the strength and resilience to do that. some of us are only a few hundred dollars away from ending up in collections, but i’m not going to stay here. watch me!

when you’re escaping an abusive relationship it will cost you everything. everything. but it will be worth it.

finances, of going from a two family income to a single family income. relationships with family and friends who only saw the highlight reels and don’t understand how this could happen because he is such a nice guy. yeah, that’s why i married him. romantic love, because honestly i do love and will always love him, but when the authorities tell you never to get back together with someone because one of you will end up dead, you listen for the sake of your kids. the institutionalized church family. i’ll leave it at that. watching my kids grieve and not understand has been the hardest by far. by far! but you know? we can’t protect our kids from pain and that isnt in the job description of being a parent. 
but you know? protecting them by teaching them resilience. providing for them. loving them. that is in the job description and i will keep doing that. 
mom is my most important title i will ever have and today and everyday, i am thankful to be raising resilient kids. we are going to be soooo good and someday i might write a book. but you know? if you think it’s ok to be abusive, stop. you do you and get the help that is available! please! families work best when they’re together. but, this message is for those victims out there. there is someone reading this today that is counting that cost and i’m going to tell you, go for it. do whatever it takes. it won’t be easy, but it will be worth it.

#abusesurvivors #raisingresilientkids 
#littlelambs #threemistersandasister #jesuslovesthelittleones  #heavenbelongstokids #longbeachwa #lifeasamommy #metoomovement #thankfulmama #inspirationeveryday #metoo

text_retweet:
in 8th grade i was sexually assaulted by a very popular classmate while everyone thought it was a joke. after the assault i ran after him and grabbed him up, immediately the principal of the school took me to his office to question why i put my hands on this gentleman . he told me that i could be in serious trouble for putting my hands on another student and that i should’ve just told the teacher. i went back to class enraged and embarrassed, i rode the bus with tears rolling down my face saying to myself “did this gentleman really put my face into his private areas” ???? the school never contacted my parents and didn’t have any consequences for the guys actions he was in my class the next day until after my parents confronted him... and yes my principal was a black male ! i was bullied and depressed for at least 2 months straight. i was called a snitch, a liar, and more! no one believed me, because he said he was giving me a “piggy back ride” (i had a bottom locker and turned back to see him jump and put his genitals in my face with as his hand pushed and grasped me towards them ... my mindset was so messed up . i can only imagine the pain #jasmineeiland may feel ! i protest because i stand for justice, i protest because i stand for my daughter, i protest because i am jasmine eiland ! if you don’t stand for something ... you will fall for anything !
.
.
.
.
.

text:
i can help you heal and never worry about hpv & cervical dysplasia ever again// my dear sister,

there is nothing more that i want than for you to feel good and empowered in your body.

with the current political climate, this desire feels more like a war-cry.

from #metoo, the unveiling of sexual assault in hollywood and beyond, the women’s march and all the women coming out of the woodwork to express their truth, i truly feel like a global shift if occurring.

it is time for women to be sovereign in the body’s experiences and choices.

it is time for women to reconnect to their bodies for their sake, and for the sake of all the women who came before who could not.

healing the cervix is healing our ancestral wounds, for all the memory of that which has penetrated us is stored in the cervix. that means, for thousands of generations our mothers and grandmothers stored their memories in their cervixes, but never had the chance to heal them.

this changes with us, and i can help you.

i know i can help you.

i can help you reconnect to your cervix and love your body in a way that you never knew possible.

i can help you become informed and aware of the health of your cervix, and how it relates to the health of your whole body and being.

i can help you feel empowered in your gynecological experiences so that you never feel disempowered, overcome, terrified or alone in the process.

you're not alone.

millions of women are experiencing this alongside you, and together, we can change the narrative and heal our disconnection to this very, very sacred body part.

and so please, dear sister, head to the link in my bio to learn how this information will transform your life and experience in the gynecologist’s office.

i am sending out the war-cry.

are you ready to receive it?

with fervent love,

xoxo
denell

text:
texto: cuidado com os heróis que tiram a roupa

imagine você, com uma hérnia de disco, imagine se você tenha um filho "nas drogas", imagina você com depressão, imagina você que sofreu um abuso sexual, imagine você que está com imensos problemas financeiros e que nunca são resolvidos.....imagina você cheio de dores emocionais e físicas. e se você soubesse que existe uma pessoa que tem verdadeiros poderes espirituais e que está realmente curando muitas pessoas?
o que você faria? iria atrás dessa pessoa.
agora imagina, você pai ou mãe, levando sua filha amada para ser tratada por essa pessoa. que felicidade. vocês chegam no lugar, há muitas pessoas esperando tratamento, todas estão de branco, você se senta com sua filha, espera a hora de sua filha ser atentida por essa pessoa maravilhosa
o nome de sua filha é anunciado. ela se levanta esperançosa e feliz. 
não pai, você não precisa entrar com ela, ela entra sozinha- é o que dizem para você.
ela entra na sala.
você espera. segundos, minutos passam e você ansioso para ver sua filha saindo radiante daquela sala.
e ela sai.
mas você nota algo estranho em seu olhar, como se ela quisesse gritar, como quando ela está com medo do sapo que apareceu na varanda. e você pai, bem sabe quando ela está assustada. você vai ao encontro dela, ela agarra forte tua mão, e você percebe que o que ela apenas quer é sair de lá.
entram no carro. e o seu mundo pai, desaba. 
aquele ser maravilhoso e curador, chamado de medium espiritual, obrigou sua filha nos momentos que estava a sós com ela a realizar sexo oral nele. ele tocou no corpo, ele abusou o corpo dela.
pai, eu sei, eu imagino a dor, eu imagino o ódio que você pode sentir. 
continua: www.quemlêasaparências.com

text:
it's your, check engine light on, too? in recovery, we need to take stock often of what's going on with us and why. in the process, we just might discover something new, even after years of recovery... during recovery group this week, i asked the ladies if they had ever avoided reaching out when they needed to. all but one had, which is shocking (women in recovery of any form often feel like a burden and bother). i was surprised, because i knew she wasn't reaching out early in recovery nearly as often as she needed, to me or the other women in group. so we got curious about that.

funny how the truth comes out... "i just didn't call you because i didn't want you to call me out! then i would have to work on it. ugh!" wait...wha?!?!?!? we all had a pretty good laugh, and the other women all nodded their heads or voiced agreement. it was a fun moment of bonding for all of us.

i think that's pretty common; we don't always want to be honest or take responsibility for ourselves right away. often as women, it goes deeper--we don't feel capable or worthy of a better life, so we stay stuck. maybe we don't even realize how happy we'll feel once we are really willing to change for the better and truly understand how our actions/beliefs/fears are causing the saddness, depression and anxiety.

so i got serious about how i might "not reach out" when it feels uncomfortable. after 19 years in recovery, there are still things i'd rather not think about (ahem, the budget or retirement....) often, the worry and avoidance is more troublesome than actually tackling the issue. therefore, i'll be balancing the checkbook today.

are you avoiding anything? if so, i want to challenge you to get clear on it, maybe even share what you are going to do here for a little accountability. then, get to it! you'll be so gald when it's over.

text:
stop calling little girls and young women fast! it is very important for a young girl or woman to feel comfortable in her own skin and love her body without her entire identity being formed around her looks. a lot of the time- unless she was sexually violated- a little girl is not even thinking about sex or being physically intimate with someone! but as people call her “fast”, “loose” and other hurtful names she starts to think something is wrong with her, it instills fear and guilt, and sometimes she may even begin acting out based on who she now believes that she is. as parents, family members, educators, spiritual leaders, friends and an overall community we have to stop making girls feel ashamed about their bodies and stop raising them in unhealthy environments that breed low self-esteem and predatory behavior.

text:
🌻”i am a survivor” — @iamkatperez. #iamasurvivor 
__
claiming this part of my identity because it’s been such a part of me that i used to hate owning as part of me. i used to feel claiming the word survivor made me weak, because in my mind it meant admitting to all the times i felt so powerless & weak and because it ultimately meant acknowledging that yes, i was a victim of violence & it has impacted every aspect of my life.
__
claiming the word has made me realize the power in the word “survivor” is about accepting the reality of what i’ve been through & loving the parts of me who have been through hell & figured out how to survive under difficult circumstances.
—
i realized all the coping strategies i developed as a result of abuses i’ve been through helped me in my past, one of which was silence, helped me make it out alive & to get by in the world & even when those chose not to help & when i tried to speak up as a child. but, silence no longer serves me or others suffering or those who are just unaware.
—
i will not censor myself or my story with silence.
__
i will continue speaking up, sharing my truth, my story in bigger & bolder ways with the strong intention to continue on my healing journey & sharing tools of empowerment & invite the world to heal because this phenomenon of abuse is a global issue i intend to help transmute in my lifetime with the power of truth & love.
__
i choose to be seen. be heard. be true. be love.
__
#beseen #beheard #betrue #belove

text:
wenn wir ein trauma erlitten haben, erfahrungen die verletzen und zerstören, die ihren schweif durch die folgende zeit ziehen, brauchen wir genau dieses licht und verständnis unserer mitmenschen, derjenigen die uns wichtig sind. dabei geht es nicht um ständige hilfe, therapie und gespräche, austausch und kompensation. manchmal geht es einfach nur darum von jemandem das gefühl vermittelt zu bekommen, in einem schützenden umfeld zu sein und vor wiederholungen, erinnerungen und der selbstzerstörung bewahrt zu werden. wir hoffen nicht auf hilfe, sondern schutz, nicht darauf alles erzählen zu müssen, sondern einfach darauf,  bewahrt zu werden. 
#trauma #lichterkette #schatten #hilfe #schutzengel #verständnis #psychologie #mindset #mind #menschen #verletzt #spreadlove #metoo #love #liebe #lifegoeson #life

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf

text: 8:01pm a few hrs ago i had to make a call. i needed help. i dropped another plate and it set me off. both my hands have nerve damage from a domestic fight i was in a few years back. that fight followed a sexual trauma with the same person that still has me pretty fucked up...but for some specific reasons: i want to be over all of it. i swear on that shit. but i have permanent reminders of a lot of my pain. i drop a plate? it takes me to my darkest times. i want to be over all of it...but my friends hang out with him. i want to be over it. but he works in some of the same spaces as me and it makes it hard for me to. ive been told my words fuck up his rep...could ruin his life...could affect his career...his family. but what about mine? i want to get over it but my blatent cries for help were mocked. gossiped about. and i was shunned. i want to get over it but every single time i look at my face, i see physical reminders of my pain. i want to get over it but im angry that i wrap my arms around every.fucking.body. all the time...even when i barely have anything to give...and barely anyone wrapped their arms around me when i needed it. my self-worth took a downward plunge that i cant believe i came back from. i want to get over it but #metoo. i want to get over it but everywhere i turn people are talking about everyones pain from cosby to r kelly and how fucked up people are. theyre talking about how bad they feel for everyone that deals with verbal...emotional...physical...domestic...sexual abuse/trauma. ...feels like everyone but me. a few hours ago i had to make a call. because i needed help. i became angry about the men ive allowed to half love me (if that) bc i dont know what healthy love looks like. i became angry at myself for not demanding more for myself. i sat on my floor with a broken plate around me. just crying. so...a few hours ago i had to make a call. i needed help. and my friend said..."sit still...sit quietly...and forgive. its the only way out of this. you have to forgive him. you have to forgive them. ...and then...the most important part...you have to forgive you." i sat for an hour. forgiving. and i will continue to forgive. more love🖤.

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
sluggish, brain fog, and struggling to keep up was how i spent most of my days. mom brain is real y’all! i never felt like i had any energy and would just float through everyday just to wake up and do it all over again. i just thought that this was #momlife and how it was supposed to be. i had heard so many of my fellow oily girls rave about progressence plus+ but i’m like what i’m only 22 i’m not having hot flashes or mood swings. in november i decide to add it to my er because i was having some serious fomo. let me tell you i definitely was missing out! i have have had a huge difference in my energy levels, overall mood, and smooth shark weeks 🦈. if you use pro + tell my your oily testimony! if you aren’t you need to! trust me your hubby will thank you 😉

text:
mic test 1,2… 1,2. calling out all cheaters, calling you all out.

hard topic to talk about, and i’ve been wanting to talk about it for years. i’ve had sex with girls who were in relationships, a couple of them were married, the others in long term relationships. i’m trying not to beat around the bush here. i don’t want to muddle the word “sex” with “sexual advances” as god knows i’ve made plenty of those over my time (hey i’ve had my fair share of girls making aggressive sexual advances at #metoo). with the girls: fact is i knew what i was doing felt wrong but i went there anyways. i talk a lot and ask a lot of questions. i prefer my emotions out rather than in. more than a few times i’ve tried to bring up the deed in conversation but i’m usually faced with 1 of 2 things; 1) i’m made to feel silly for thinking anything of it! are you seriously saying you’re feeling guilty right now?! um, yes? yes i am?! 2) i’m introduced to the concept of “keeping a secret” something i’ve never done and highly doubt i could ever do.

with the guys: i’ve always had closer girl friends than guy friends. i still do. i consider my friends wives to be my mates. it hurts then to see what i’ve seen on overseas trips with the boys. when i confronted the guys about the issue i expressed that i was single, which somewhat gave me the right to do whatever i wanted, but you guys are married, with children! the response? who the fuck are you to judge justin? floored. speechless. i get it.

back to the girls again: i crossed the line once and admitted to one of the girls what her guy was doing. what was the response? shut the fuck up justin i don’t want to hear it!!! back to the guys again: just last year a mate was parading that he got a bare back blow job overseas. congratulations man, you just gave your kids an std.

i’m talking about it because everyone world wide seems to think that encouraging conversation is a great way to begin resolving big issues, but from what i’ve learned from experience; talking is the last thing the guilty want to do.

text:
i’m excited to have my piece “50 mg tramadol” in the #metoo zine by @riotgrrrlpress. 💖⚔️🧨they did an amazing job curating this zine. it is a funny, tragic, hopeful and enraging collection of art, poetry and essays that i hope everyone checks out. as an afab femme presenting person, i have dealt with a spectrum of casual misogyny to sexual violence since i was 12 years old. it’s not an unusual story, so i haven’t been super vocal about it on social media; but i am glad i was able to contribute to this collection that explores this complex topic more thoroughly than i am able to.
.
.
.

“toxic masculinity” (a term that i find increasingly insufficient) among men is rooted in the emotional underdevelopment of our boys. we tend to shame our boys for having and expressing authentic feelings and then blame our men for the resulting harmful behaviors they develop as a means of coping.  in this era of #metoo can we acknowledge that and collectively decide to do better by our boys?💞

text: i’m suffering from online dating withdrawal syndrome. odws. i might have made it up, but it’s a thing, i swear. i gave up online dating a month ago and have been feeling down ever since. it always gave me something to do. i never got bored. #swipe swipe swipe i flirted, bantered, got attention, got annoyed, got disgusted, but i stayed busy. and suddenly, all of that was gone and there was a void. i blamed my #sadness on this and on that, but yesterday it occurred to me, i normally have at least someone in the queue and there’s no one. what’s worse, there’s not even a prospect of a someone because i have no place to meet anyone. on the bright side, since  understanding why i’ve been in a funk, i’ve already been using my time more productively, so that feels good. that’s why i wanted to let you know, if you go cold turkey on those ole #datingapps keep in mind that you might feel an absence, a withdrawal, if you will. it’s very easy to fix, all you have to do is go back online and create a new profile, but try and stick with it. message me instead! i know it isn’t the same, but at least we can keep each other preoccupied. you can also watch my videos at sugarpunch.co 🍹link in bio

text:
i don’t talk about this a lot.... .
watching the series you “on netflix” got me thinking too.
.
as a female trainer unfortunately i’ve had my experience with sexual harassment. i get it, on social media➡️ the trolls, weird guys that hop on my lives and 🍆 pics galore and stalker like behavior .
.
i think a lot of times we are to scared to speak up when we think something “isn’t right” i was too and still had a rather salty experience when i did 😕
.
.
however the kind of harassment i’ve had was with ➡️ bosses, male clients and co workers. i remember harassment getting so bad that i use to have a co worker walk me to a car in fear for me having these people waiting for me.
.
.
i had a male client who developed an obsession with me. he would ask me where i was, what i was doing,
comment on my body sexually during our training sessions “get aroused” clearly 🍆 and i felt forced to train him because i had to “make budget/ sales “quotas for this gym... i remember being fed up and told my boss. .
.
he told me ➡️ that’s just what attractive females have to deal with. appalled ➡️embarrassed i continued to deal with it. luckily i had a co worker step in and say this isn’t okay after i told them about the sexual pictures this male client would send me. .
.
sexual harassment isn’t funny, it’s not cute and is not something you should have to deal with. my boss only cared about numbers and not me and my safety. i felt like i fool for telling anyone but i knew i needed to 😔 .
.
if you feel like something is crossing the line you’re probably right. i get it ➡️ the gym is a male dominated world and no not all my male clients were like this “just one ☝🏻 “ was. .
.
you shouldn’t be scared to train at the gym let alone go to work. please speak up. you deserved to be safe and respected no matter what your profession is .
.
have you experienced harassment before 🙇🏼‍♀️
.
.

text:
check out my instagram stories and see all the fun prizes i got myself for hitting my first fitness goals of 2019! ⁣
⁣
goal: reduce binge eating with a food diary, talk about my feelings instead of eating them, consistently show up for 6 weeks of workouts (5 days per week), talk to myself with a whole lot of love and grace. ⁣
⁣
i would say the work i’ve done over the last 6 weeks has been some of my best. particularly because my goals were not related to a number on the scale or the size of my pants. ⁣
⁣
coach stephie juice tip: shift the focus of your fitness goals from the symptom to the issue. the issue of weight gain is not typically the problem, the problem is what is causing it... poor diet, inconsistency, binge eating, stress? those are the things that need to be tackled. otherwise... you will just keep getting the same result and you’ll likely never be satisfied for more than a short term few moments when you hit the magic number on the scale. ⁣
⁣
retrain your brain to support your life in a healthy and loving way. ⁣
you deserve that. and if you want to lose weight or wear a smaller pant size that’s ok! but you still deserve to love yourself through the process. ⁣

⁣
goal: reduce binge eating with a food diary, talk about my feelings instead of eating them, consistently show up for 6 weeks of workouts (5 days per week), talk to myself with a whole lot of love and grace. ⁣
⁣
i would say the work i’ve done over the last 6 weeks has been some of my best. particularly because my goals were not related to a number on the scale or the size of my pants. ⁣
⁣
coach stephie juice tip: shift the focus of your fitness goals from the symptom to the issue. the issue of weight gain is not typically the problem, the problem is what is causing it... poor diet, inconsistency, binge eating, stress? those are the things that need to be tackled. otherwise... you will just keep getting the same result and you’ll likely never be satisfied for more than a short term few moments when you hit the magic number on the scale. ⁣

their ask of me? 
to share my #experienceofgod!

topics i speak and #teach on are:
#image, #style, #personalbrand #identity, #success, hope, #overcoming, #domesticviolence #metoo #feartofreedom, and faith

do you sometimes feel that people put you in a box as to who you are? 
when it comes to your identity and #visionofsuccess -your #purpose -don’t let people put you in a box as to what you can and cannot do! 
it was just a few short years ago when i was told, “you can’t talk on this topic and that one too”, and yet, i am doing exactly what i set out to do as a speaker, trainer, and coach! 
my body of work supports the #wholeintegratedyou
and i can #champion you to #crossthefinishline because i first said, #yes to championing myself! 
drown out the noise of the #naysayers and #keepyoureyeontheprize!
xo 💃🏿

text:
sarah blum, a vietnam veteran and author of women under fire: abuse in the military, writes our latest sound off blog article, detailing the harrowing realities of sexual assault in the military, the retaliation against those who report it, and the lack of possible legal remedies that victims have due to the #feresdoctrine. .
.
“how can it be that members of our military who put their lives in the line for all of us have no recourse when raped or sexually assaulted in the line of duty? how can the judges who rule on the feres doctrine be blind to the injustice they are perpetrating? these judges are standing with military sexual predators when they rule that rape is ‘incident to service.’”

text: did you know that the #metoo movement didn’t begin with a celebrity tweet in 2017? it actually began 20 years earlier in 1997, when a 13 year old girl told tarana burke, a black woman, about being sexually abused. burke was haunted by the story. 10 years later, she founded a non profit organization to support sexual assault and harassment victims. she also founded a movement and named it metoo. a woman of color, a non celebrity, far from hollywood, originally coined the now familiar phrase.

text:
part one: the women’s locker room. .
.
. 
today after a glorious hour of cardio dance, followed by a soothing steam and shower, i was basking in my after workout wonder in the locker room. standing proudly in my panties, i tended to my hair, admired my body and sat atop the post workout mountain i had just climbed. success was surrounding me and i was so happy to feel liberated amongst my fellow women - to be with my body in a natural way. two effervescent girls were chatting, laughter was in the air and the place was abundant with endorphins. grateful. .
.
.

these two girls took a vulnerable turn, and one by one the ladies of the locker room lost their buzz. subconsciously, we all tuned in as they disclosed their realities. the energy from this conversation was seething. their pride, dignity, body and jobs had been stolen from them. one began to confide in the other about being a 19-year-old female with her 35-year-old senior manager harassing her. she felt she couldn’t tell anyone at work and everything she was doing wasn’t being taken seriously. he had crossed so many lines she had finally decided her only option was to quit. she was a server: beautiful, young, and condemned. her friend responded with sympathy and then began to remind her of a situation that happened to her at her last job, “remember when i had to quit my job at **** because my manager was doing the same thing… it sucks but that’s just part of being a server.” photo credit: @skipischris

text:
part two:

at this point, i looked down and noticed my hands were shaking. i was in shock from anger and lifted my head to look around. the look on every single, silent, disturbed woman’s face in the room was united. all inaudible, all together. the girls confiding hadn’t noticed the darkness or depth that was being brought out of everyone through their disclosures. don’t make eye contact. we cannot let anyone else see. this experience could not have, should not have… how did it happened to me. please. don’t. remind. me. why. can’t. i. breathe. with shaky hands and even shakier voice, i mustered the strength and peeked around the lockers to approach them. apprehensively, i apologized for intruding but said i just needed a moment of their time. i told them that it was not only unfair, but just fucking wrong what was happening and had happened to them. i told them there are tons of resources to help move through situations like this. i told them that they weren’t alone, and if they needed resources or help, to take my contact information and that i could help connect them. then i told them that i understand whole heartedly if they don’t want to say anything, but if you don’t act at all, think of the other girls who will come after. you could see the lights come on in both their eyes. one of them said, “i had never even thought about that.” i told them i was there if they needed, then slunk away. i couldn’t stomach saying much more as i could feel my throat closing and tears coming through as i finished speaking. .
.
.

text: very proud to be sharing this work created in collaboration with @micaela_mamede for her awe inspiring choreography performance at gibney dance, this is #maria2018. produced and performed by an ensemble of non-us immigrant women and allies, maria tells the all too common story of violence and silence immigrant women face. this whole project was made possible by micaela and her unwavering visual mission to share her own voice. she's since gained the support of the #healmetoo festival, a grassroots foundation working to heal victims of sexual violence by funding creative, therapeutic outlets for victims. please join us at the first ever nyc heal me too festival march 27-april 19, 2019. to learn more about their work, please follow @micaela_mamede and @healmetoofest and visit www.healmetoofest.com #metoo #womenshistorymonth #intimatepartnerviolence #healing - makeup by @batamakeup and cast: #danutapetrow-sek #emilyteller #hayetmoutfi, #krishnawashburn #malaikacambridge #maluavalos #mariasek #micaelamamede and #pearlbhatnagar - thank you ladies. xo

text:
when it comes to instagram, i feel like i’m on xfactor and simon cowell is telling me i’ve picked up a lot of bad habits – that my posts are a bit ‘cabaret’. given that i’ve only posted 14 times there’s a whiff of hyperbole in the air, but the overthinker in me can already tell that i’m not really nailing this insta-lark. the great thing is, i’ve decided not to care.
~
i’ve seen many fabulous grids. some are incredibly polished, others deliberately eclectic. perhaps a moody hue binds a beautiful patchwork of travel photography. maybe there is always something pink in focus – a shoe, a doughnut, pouting lips. and then there’s the filter that seems to erase reality, typical of white interiors with their pop of foliage and kubu (that scandi shit is everywhere and i bloomin’ love it). and what about the people whose gorgeousness is basically the premise for their account – their grid no more than narcissus’ pool. and why not? i’m not here to insta-shame anyone. we’re all just doing our thing. although the woman who recently posed in a swimsuit and hunter wellies in the snow ‘just for the craic’, well, i think someone needs to have a quiet word.
~
throughout my life i have always looked back and cringed. i’ve been embarrassing myself in public from a young age. i fell out of an apple tree at my sixth birthday party. as i tumbled down, my dress and knickers ripped against the branches and my friends inevitably thought it was hilarious. i didn’t cry, but my legs and arms stung with grazes and i wanted to howl.
~
more recently, i had a toe curling read through my old facebook posts before i deleted my account. yet it’s anachronistic to say these posts were silly or embarrassing because they ultimately reflected their era, a time when sarah wrote in the third person and poking people wasn’t a #metoo moment.
~
ultimately, what i’m trying to say is authenticity is better than perfection. that’s it. that is basically my white card to keep being a bit insta-shit and to use the insta-prefix even if it’s a bit cabaret to do so.
~
#throwbackthursday #xfactor #scandi #authenticself #instaperfect #cabaret #gridtastic #embarassing #whiteinteriors #hunterwellies #forthecraic

text:
✨il est venu le temps des cathédrales✨
history is cyclical. 10 years after learning about this musical, i am lacking belief that i was able to see something as legendary as this. #notredameparis is a marvel of its own, and returning to it many years after first discovery only made it richer. contrary to the lyrics, little things don’t kill large things, and we are back on the brink of time. in the age where immigration, rejection and #metoo this creation becomes so poignant. violence is alive, inequality is alive, alienation is alive and breathing. but that means, so is love.
p.s. seeing #daniellavoie live is unforgettable.

text:
good morning 💗 today is a packed day for me, mum and i are going out to get a bubble tea because she’s never tried it and i am so excited for her to because i think she’ll love it. is it weird that i’m stressed about not knowing what flavour i want? i’m feeling tropical but also there’s mango or passion fruit 😬 i have a psych later today and i have to work through memory regain before i go to court which wont be fun😓 and then tonight i have a little get together with all of my friends which i’m very excited for, my friend’s getting me from my appt and we’re doing the food shopping and prep so yay😯 hopefully it’s a nice night and i don’t overwork myself with the idea of swimming 💪 
i hope you all have/had a lovely day 💛
-addy✨

text:
#throwbackthursday to a piece i created for @drawwithjazza 's pimp my classic cotm for february 2018
.
'#metoo - a twitter spear' is a modernised twist on raphael's "st. michael vanquishing satan"
.
art & concept description below:inspired to bring the relevance of a great good vs a great evil into the modern age, i thought alyssa milano's 2017 'metoo' twitter campaign that all began with a tweet asking people to speak up was a strong modern concept.
the point of 'metoo' is to shine a light on how widespread the issue is rather than call out a particular gender or individual.
thus the blinding light of the twitter 'spear' wielded by 'archangel' (@milano_alyssa) shines down and threatens to expose a figure i consider not to be person. i chose to embody the dangers of sexual harassment and assault in the form of a popular creepy pasta monster. something faceless but you know to be wary of it.
slenderman, known to abduct, traumatise and manipulate but not truly known in pop culture to kill was the ideal metaphor to replace lucifer. his hooked and grasping tentacles weave around the angel but are ultimately powerless against the light - cringing away at its touch as he is pinned to the ground.
.
#trixks #art #artistsoninstagram #digitalart #tbt #illustration #artchallenge #artoftheday #challenge #pimpmyclassic #fantasyart #slenderman #archangel #angel

text:
it's easy to get sucked into feeling like nothing can go right, especially if you've been in an abusive relationship. i know because i've been there. but guess what? you don't have to stay there. you deserve to live the best life possible. you deserve to have great experiences, a hopeful future, and plain ol' happiness. 😀
the fact that you've been broken simply means that now you've been opened up to do more, accept more, love more and live more. embrace that! 
#domesticviolence #dvsurvivor #metoo #domesticviolencewareness

#narcissisticabuse

text:
6 months ago i was at my worst. 6 months ago i was drowning everything that was ever given to me, literally and figuratively. i have never been so low or in so much pain in my life. i had never been treated as badly, or been in a worse place.

today i was able to wake up, get up,  go to work for 9 hours, and i had the time of my life. i'm happy. i have all i need at the moment, and i'm just thankful. i feel good about myself and it's only getting better!
cheers to accepting where we are. no matter where that is, and no matter what has happened to you. you can still be happy, because we're not defined by our past. 💙

p.s. we're also never defined by a diagnosis or an experience. you are you because you choose you. no one can tell you who you are.
#survivor #lymedisease #bpd #metoo #werule

text:
yo te creo, por supuesto que te creo hoy, ayer y mañana. a ti, a la vecina y a aquella de la que jamás he oído hablar.

te creo porque yo he sido tú, porque cuando no he sido tú, he visto cómo lo era mi hermana, mi prima o mi compañera de clase. te creo porque a veces no hace falta que termines de contar tu relato para saber cómo sigue. te creo porque son básicos, es tan básico su modus operandi que es difícil no encasillarlos rápidamente. es difícil no saber cuál va a ser el siguiente paso cuando conoces e identificas el ciclo del maltrato.

y esque son tan malos, y se les da tan mal ser machos, que no saben salir del patrón, no son capaces de ver que maltratam porque no saben ni pensar. igual pensar si, pero no empatizar. no tienen ni idea de lo que es ser mujer, con o sin ovarios. no tenéis ni idea de que el ser mujer siempre es un plus de vulnerabilidad y yo doy gracias por haber nacido mujer pero joder, qué duro se hace a veces el camino. y no es que no lo sepan por no vivirlo, es que no quieren saberlo. no quieren pensar que el mero hecho de nacer hombre les regala un plus de privilegios sociales. porque si reconocen sus privilegios, se verán obligados a renunciar a ellos, y eso sí que no. voy a la mani del 8m pero la camisa la plancha mi madre!

pues si hermana yo te creo y estoy aquí, como todas nuestras compañeras, para dejarnos la piel hasta que nadie nos tenga que creer. hasta que la equidad de género se haya logrado y todo esto sea un recuerdo.

pero no solo te creo a ti, hermana con un cuerpo normativo, blanca, heterosexual. 
os creo a todas cuando decís que el feminismo peca de racismo y capacitismo, y cuando mi cabeza automáticamente duda más os creo, porque son mis privilegios los que me hacen dudar de vuestra palabra, que no se oye nítida desde arriba. 
os creo a todas porque también me costó creerme a mi, también me costó luchar con mis fantasmas y los de mi entorno para entender que no estaba loca. que no eran mis paranoias y que algo estaba fallando en este sistema.

yo te creo hermana y aquí tienes mi mano que ahora es tuya, que más que pertenecerme pertenece a todas, porque somos manada y vamos a vencer.

#yotecreo #metoo #sororidad

text:
i don’t know. 🤷🏽‍♂️ maybe it’s how i was raised. maybe it’s because i have four women in my household. maybe it’s because i grew up with all sisters. or maybe it’s just because i am a decent man like some of us out here. i don’t know, but i’m just sick of it. all i know is this. men that disrespect women by only seeing them as eye candy makes me want to lay hands on them........and pray. 🙏🏾 🥊 ➖
any man who only focuses on the physical attributes of a woman is shallow and baseless. he lacks depth. especially when said man has not formed any type of relationship whatsoever with said woman. you are unauthorized, my guy. and even if you have formed a legitimate relationship, you are still unauthorized until you are authorized...my guy. 🏌🏾
➖
there is so much more to our sisters than what meets the eye. real men understand that. over the years i‘ve become more and more annoyed by all of the stories i’ve heard from countless women who have been flat out disrespected by these clowns. i have a wife and three daughters. i haven’t had many issues with cats coming for my wife. maybe my demeanor says “not so” 🙅🏽‍♂️ or something. but if my daughters ever inform me that they have experienced the types of things i’ve seen and heard from other women over the years, i will need an immediate prayer meeting.
➖
fellas, don’t comment on her body if you aren’t interested in her brains. don’t drop in those dm’s unless you care about her dreams. stop acting like you care about her interests when you know it’s all a ploy. stop lying and spitting game knowing you have nothing but bad intentions. we owe our sisters more than that. sorry if i messed up anyone’s game (not for real). cut it out and let’s be better, gentlemen.
➖
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text_retweet:
🔗link in my bio🔗
i had become addicted to the emotional rollercoaster that black sent me on. i struggled to understand why i was still there. what would make me stay with someone who obviously didn’t give a fuck about me. he’d tell me that i was “the only bitch” that he ever had to be. i was “hard headed and wouldn’t listen” therefore he had to teach me. the abuse wasn’t always physical, he would mentally tear me to pieces, but he was great at pretending to be everything that i needed. he’d tell me that without him i would never succeed or be anything more than a bum bitch, then shower me with affection telling me that i meant the world to him. as much as i was addicted to oxy, i was addicted to him and craved his approval. black would gaslight me, control me, and then show love, backing me into a corner blaming myself for being inadequate. then i’d be desperate to win back his love and attention. i was so bonded with him and my emotions, that i continued to come back every time. black was a narcissist and i was co-dependent that was plagued with the need to be with him to the point that i felt like i would die without him, so i might as well die with him. it took me two years, 6 months, and 5 days to realize how much my life was worth and that he did not value it in the least. .
.
.
.
.

text:
so, we’re introducing you to this 👑 today. elon, a true icon, is dominating advocacy on maternal and infant justice. more about her below 👇🏽 .
.
.
elon has been a birth doula since 2016, she came to doula work "accidentally" after being a home visitor for a local health department. through that experience she discovered that many women she provided services to were experiencing isolation during pregnancy and lacked positive psycho-social support lending to negative birth experiences. in partnership with local health department leadership and community members, she advocated for a dona community wide doula training and walked away with a practical skills and a deeper appreciation for the value of doula advocacy, particularly, for women of color.  while maintaining a private doula practice, elon has served as project coordinator, statewide speaker and consultant with a number of public health projects but finds her greatest joys in serving women as they transition into motherhood and fostering change in attitudes, policy and practice around pregnancy, labor and birth.  elon received her formal education from michigan state university where she studied physiology and health studies with a cognate in psychology. she is a certified parent educator (effective black parenting), certified childbirth educator (icea), trained in lamaze childbirth education and is a certified lactation consultant (alpp). .
#mpdi #momsbeyondbars #prisondoula #doula #childbirth #birthdoula #midwife #socialjustice #blessed #whynotme #takeactuon #standup #speakout #useyourvoice #woman #womensrights #metoo #humanrights #prison #michigan #criminaljusticereform #criminaljusticereform #proud #bethechange #impact #activism #womanempowerment #justiceforall #massincarceration #togetherwecan #community

text:
i was attacked on my way home from work tonight.

it was 6:20pm. i’d just left the office and i was walking down a deserted road - the same road i walked down this morning, listening to @theguiltyfeminist podcast and feeling all #strongindependentwoman

a group of boys appeared around the corner. one of them came to within a few inches of me and screamed in my face, clearly looking for a reaction. this has happened before with the same group, so i knew what was coming and didn’t react. but they hadn’t got what they wanted, so the rest of the group gathered around me and started jeering and laughing. then one of them shoved me and i stumbled over. having succeeded in humiliating me sufficiently, they left.

i’m not hurt. they were kids looking for a laugh, and trying to show off in front of their mates. as far as assault goes, i know this wasn’t “that bad” - people go through far, far worse.

and yet i’m shaken. i just spent half an hour crying down the phone to my friend (and i’m not normally a crier). i kept saying i’m fine but i’m not really fine. i’ve been catcalled and whistled at, and i’ve had people press against me on the tube, but this is the first time i’ve received physical violence. this is not a list of feminist badges, this is the daily reality for many women around the world. i’m astounded that it’s 2019 and yet it’s not safe to walk down the streets of london as a woman.

my friend encouraged me to share this on instagram, if nothing else to raise awareness that sexism is still very real, and feminism very much needed. now i’m going to have a massive bowl of pasta and watch netflix. we are not the weaker sex. 💪🏻 #metoo

text:
everyday conversation is peppered with habitual sexism, conscious or unconscious. i’m raising awareness because i owe it to my younger self, the self who was sexually harassed in the workplace. it started as banter, jokey comments, an arm around the shoulder, a bear hug, soft sweet talking, that became flirtatious. then it became shouting, passive aggressive, bullying, and controlling. picking me up from behind and squeezing me tight, in front of a room full of staff. blocking my exit from an office, and invading my personal space. it lasted 5 years. and i watched it happen to others. you may say why did i not do anything? each day i put on my armour and i found a way to keep going by blocking out what was really happening. i didn’t know it was sexual harassment, this type of behaviour was accepted as normal. eventually i broke and i walked away from a profitable business. i will continue to raise awareness because everyday language peppered with habitual sexism, may lead to worse, if condoned and left to manifest. it happens. it’s not ok. and it’s ok to say it’s not ok. .
.
if you are at all in question about ‘is this sexual harassment’, check out on @bbciplayer the real life experiment scenario ‘is this sexual harassment and discover blurred lines, and how to recognise what is legally deemed sexual harassment @bbcone it’s an eye opener. and discussion starter. i’ve written a blog post. link to the programme in bio. 👆🏻👆🏻👆🏻
.
.
.
.
#pressforprogress #raisingawareness #callitout #bethechange #womenempowerment #wearefuturefemale #metoo #metoomovement #sexualharrassment #womensupportwomen #bbc

i’m trying to get dad to get me out on saturday. i’m not going to be vey happy if they keep me in this weekend!
